1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,500
I've heard stories, but I never imagined it would be like this.

2
00:00:04,160 --> 00:00:05,320
This place holds secrets.

3
00:00:06,500 --> 00:00:07,880
I know it.

4
00:00:09,260 --> 00:00:10,540
She only needed one interview.

5
00:00:11,080 --> 00:00:14,260
Jago  Quint  was  the  billionaire  no  one  could  reach,  and  that

6
00:00:14,260 --> 00:00:15,660
story  could  save  her  career.

7
00:00:16,120 --> 00:00:19,360
So  she  accepted  the  most  dangerous  deal  of  her  life,  pretending

8
00:00:19,360 --> 00:00:20,860
to  be  his  girlfriend  for  one

9
00:00:20,860 --> 00:00:21,260
night.

10
00:00:21,620 --> 00:00:22,940
It was supposed to be simple.

11
00:00:23,420 --> 00:00:26,520
Walk  into  the  ball  convinces  family  and  walk  out  with  the  answers  she

12
00:00:26,520 --> 00:00:27,640
needed,  but  when

13
00:00:27,640 --> 00:00:30,960
Jago's  mother  demanded  proof  of  love  in  front  of  everyone,  she

14
00:00:30,960 --> 00:00:31,900
did  exactly  what  she

15
00:00:31,900 --> 00:00:32,700
shouldn't have.

16
00:00:32,940 --> 00:00:33,800
She kissed Jago.

17
00:00:34,320 --> 00:00:37,060
And  that  kiss,  which  was  only  supposed  to  be  a  lie,

18
00:00:37,640 --> 00:00:39,320
started  to  feel  far  too  real.

19
00:00:41,990 --> 00:00:42,510
Hi, I'm Rowan.

20
00:00:42,870 --> 00:00:45,870
A  special  shout  out  to  those  of  you  watching  Book  One  for  free  here  on  the

21
00:00:45,870 --> 00:00:46,850
My  Stories  platform,

22
00:00:47,350 --> 00:00:49,410
completely ad-free and uninterrupted.

23
00:00:51,720 --> 00:00:52,380
Chapter 1.

24
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:54,040
The Impossible Interview.

25
00:00:55,580 --> 00:00:58,860
His  room  smelled  of  reheated  coffee  and  old  paper,  and

26
00:00:58,860 --> 00:01:00,820
Rowina  Pike  had  already  drunk  three

27
00:01:00,820 --> 00:01:02,380
cups before nine in the morning.

28
00:01:02,880 --> 00:01:07,600
The gray light coming through the window gave every face there the same shade of exhaustion.

29
00:01:08,200 --> 00:01:12,900
The kind of fatigue that doesn't come from one bad night's sleep, but from months piled

30
00:01:12,900 --> 00:01:14,280
one on top of another.

31
00:01:14,620 --> 00:01:16,580
She knew, hers was no different.

32
00:01:17,020 --> 00:01:21,520
She held her folder against her chest, and crossed the narrow aisle between the desks,

33
00:01:21,920 --> 00:01:24,220
greeting with a Kurt Nord anyone who looked up.

34
00:01:24,480 --> 00:01:28,760
Hollis Vaughn was waiting for her with his elbows planted on the desk, glasses pushed

35
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:29,860
to the tip of his nose.

36
00:01:29,860 --> 00:01:34,780
The editor had a peculiar way of looking at people, as if he were checking whether they were

37
00:01:34,780 --> 00:01:35,860
worth their own salary.

38
00:01:36,440 --> 00:01:40,960
Rowina shut the door behind her, ignored the chair he didn't offer, and sat down without

39
00:01:40,960 --> 00:01:41,980
waiting for an invitation.

40
00:01:42,500 --> 00:01:43,880
I need the interview Pike.

41
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:48,560
Hollis didn't waste time on introductions, and I need something else too.

42
00:01:48,840 --> 00:01:52,420
If you're about to tell me you need a photo of Quint without his jacket, I'm walking

43
00:01:52,420 --> 00:01:53,800
out of this room right now.

44
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:55,000
I need a file.

45
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:59,660
The sentence landed in the middle of the desk, like something too heavy for the furniture.

46
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:05,140
Rowina raised an eyebrow, waiting for him to refraise to apologise to turn it into a joke.

47
00:02:05,620 --> 00:02:06,900
Hollis did none of that.

48
00:02:07,100 --> 00:02:11,860
He simply laced his fingers, and kept looking at her, as if he were collecting on an old

49
00:02:11,860 --> 00:02:12,160
debt.

50
00:02:12,660 --> 00:02:16,820
Proof, he added, that that empire is hiding something it shouldn't be hiding.

51
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:18,780
Everyone hides something Pike.

52
00:02:19,140 --> 00:02:20,520
You just need to find out what?

53
00:02:20,520 --> 00:02:25,080
You want me to get inside the home of the most closed off family in the south.

54
00:02:25,320 --> 00:02:29,840
Land the interview no one's managed to land in 10 years, and still walk out of there with

55
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:30,820
compromising material.

56
00:02:31,340 --> 00:02:33,920
I'm telling you that your job here depends on it.

57
00:02:34,100 --> 00:02:35,440
She didn't answer right away.

58
00:02:35,660 --> 00:02:38,200
She sat staring at the coffee stain on the rim of his mug.

59
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:43,300
Calculating how much of next month's salary was already committed to rent, how much was

60
00:02:43,300 --> 00:02:44,780
still owed on her mother's bill.

61
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:48,180
The window behind Hollis let in the muffled noise of the street.

62
00:02:48,180 --> 00:02:50,100
A horn, a quick step.

63
00:02:50,500 --> 00:02:54,500
The city running nonstop while she sat there deciding how far she was willing to go.

64
00:02:54,860 --> 00:02:59,260
Then she nodded once, short, like someone signing a contract they haven't yet read.

65
00:02:59,820 --> 00:03:04,240
Malo Trent intercepted her in the hallway with two fresh coffees, and a smile that was

66
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:05,080
already a question.

67
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:10,580
Malo was a copy editor, a colleague of three years, and the only person in the newsroom

68
00:03:10,580 --> 00:03:15,540
who understood when Rowine needed silence, and when she needed noise, you look like someone

69
00:03:15,540 --> 00:03:16,900
who just sold her soul.

70
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:19,420
Malo remarked, handing over the hotter cup.

71
00:03:19,820 --> 00:03:20,480
Was it for much?

72
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:22,400
It was for next month's rent.

73
00:03:23,040 --> 00:03:28,260
Malo laughed, a short laugh, cut off halfway by the awareness that the joke was worth

74
00:03:28,260 --> 00:03:30,120
more to herself than to Rowine.

75
00:03:30,640 --> 00:03:35,000
She leaned her shoulder against Rowine as they walked down the hallway, and for a moment,

76
00:03:35,540 --> 00:03:40,140
Rowine felt like dropping everything right there, walking out the front door and never

77
00:03:40,140 --> 00:03:40,800
coming back.

78
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:41,840
She didn't.

79
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:44,260
She drank the coffee until it burned her tongue.

80
00:03:44,260 --> 00:03:48,360
After noon came quickly, and with it a note left at the front desk.

81
00:03:48,760 --> 00:03:53,740
No sender, just her name on the front of the envelope, written in black pen and handwriting

82
00:03:53,740 --> 00:03:59,360
that wasn't a friend, slanted controlled letters, each one in its exact place.

83
00:03:59,900 --> 00:04:04,540
Rowine had turned the envelope over twice before opening it, inside just an address and

84
00:04:04,540 --> 00:04:05,100
a time.

85
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:06,140
Nothing more.

86
00:04:06,460 --> 00:04:11,200
The office it pointed to was three blocks away, in a discreet building she had never noticed,

87
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:13,960
despite having walked past it hundreds of times.

88
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:18,800
The sign at the entrance simply read Ashford and Associates, in letters too small to

89
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:19,400
draw attention.

90
00:04:20,080 --> 00:04:24,040
Rowine aclimed the steps with her folder still pressed against her chest, and greeted

91
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:26,180
the receptionist with the name that was on the note.

92
00:04:26,660 --> 00:04:29,000
The man who received her was younger than she expected.

93
00:04:29,580 --> 00:04:34,000
Tall, navy, suit, no tie, with that kind of discretion only old money teachers.

94
00:04:34,520 --> 00:04:39,160
He extended his hand and introduced himself as Silas Ashford, the Quint family's lawyer,

95
00:04:39,160 --> 00:04:41,880
a friend of Jago's since their boarding school days.

96
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:46,480
The information came without fanfare, the way someone hands over a business card.

97
00:04:46,980 --> 00:04:47,920
Have a seat, Miss Pike.

98
00:04:48,440 --> 00:04:51,000
His voice had the same tone as the handwriting on the envelope.

99
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:53,520
I'll be brief because the proposal is brief.

100
00:04:53,980 --> 00:04:54,580
I'm curious.

101
00:04:55,260 --> 00:04:59,000
Mr. Quint agrees to grant a two-hour interview to your publication.

102
00:04:59,620 --> 00:05:01,480
No restrictions on subject matter.

103
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:02,640
Except one.

104
00:05:03,140 --> 00:05:04,620
Silas made a minimal pause.

105
00:05:04,620 --> 00:05:09,060
The kind of pause lawyers used to let the client swallow the next piece of information.

106
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:14,700
In return, you would attend the family's Gallaboll in Savannah as his companion on Friday.

107
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:17,020
One night, just one.

108
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:20,340
Rowine elapsed before her brain authorized her mouth.

109
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:21,600
Companion.

110
00:05:22,180 --> 00:05:23,400
That's the word he preferred.

111
00:05:23,980 --> 00:05:25,560
And what word didn't he prefer?

112
00:05:26,100 --> 00:05:30,500
The corner of Silas's mouth moved half a millimeter, almost the beginning of a smile,

113
00:05:30,660 --> 00:05:31,840
but nothing followed through.

114
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:36,600
He slid a black envelope across the desk, sealed, with her name written on the front,

115
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:40,300
in the same slanted, controlled handwriting as the first note.

116
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:42,740
Letters she now recognized without effort,

117
00:05:43,160 --> 00:05:45,600
and which definitely did not belong to Silas.

118
00:05:46,100 --> 00:05:47,240
The rules are in there.

119
00:05:47,460 --> 00:05:48,440
One read is enough.

120
00:05:48,820 --> 00:05:50,180
The expects an answer today.

121
00:05:50,740 --> 00:05:52,920
Rowine looked at the black envelope for too long.

122
00:05:53,280 --> 00:05:54,480
She thought about the rent.

123
00:05:54,880 --> 00:05:57,060
She thought about the look on Holasis face.

124
00:05:57,340 --> 00:06:00,180
She thought about the old photograph of the reclusive billionaire

125
00:06:00,180 --> 00:06:03,040
that had circulated through the papers forever.

126
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:05,840
Always the same profile of a clenched jaw.

127
00:06:06,220 --> 00:06:09,220
Always the same gaze that didn't invite anyone to stay.

128
00:06:09,620 --> 00:06:12,700
She tucked the envelope into her folder without opening it.

129
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:14,620
Tell him I'll be in Savannah on Friday.

130
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:18,380
Silas nodded like someone who already knew the answer before the question.

131
00:06:18,900 --> 00:06:23,740
He rose, shook her hand again, and walked her to the door with practice courtesy.

132
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:26,900
Before closing the handle, he said almost without voice.

133
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:29,160
He's not what the press writes, that's all.

134
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:31,000
Rowine didn't ask what he meant.

135
00:06:31,320 --> 00:06:32,760
She preferred not to know yet.

136
00:06:33,260 --> 00:06:36,620
Marla was waiting for her on the street with a cigarette that pretended to be lit.

137
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:40,200
The kind of theatre she used as an excuse to loiter on corners.

138
00:06:40,760 --> 00:06:43,100
Rowine handed over the black envelope without ceremony.

139
00:06:43,700 --> 00:06:45,880
A friend turned the object over in her hand,

140
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:49,720
studied the seal with more attention than necessary, and gave it back.

141
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:53,060
Don't open it now, Marla said, open it on the train.

142
00:06:53,220 --> 00:06:54,100
It's prettier that way.

143
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:54,940
Pretty ya.

144
00:06:55,300 --> 00:06:57,760
Do you want to be someone else's story or make history?

145
00:06:57,760 --> 00:07:01,100
If it's the second, you open it on the train alone,

146
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:04,000
and you cry if you need to cry without anyone seeing.

147
00:07:04,460 --> 00:07:05,620
It's the least you deserve.

148
00:07:06,280 --> 00:07:08,880
Rowine laughed and the laugh pulled some of the weight off her back.

149
00:07:09,180 --> 00:07:12,040
She rested her forehead on Marla's shoulder for a short second.

150
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:15,600
Just enough to remember she still had a friend in that grey city,

151
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:17,340
and then she went home to pack.

152
00:07:17,840 --> 00:07:19,940
The station was too crowded for her taste.

153
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:22,760
Rowine had dragged her luggage between hurried bodies,

154
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:27,140
bought a sandwich she wasn't going to eat, and settled by the window of the car.

155
00:07:27,140 --> 00:07:30,460
The seats smelled of dust and warm synthetic leather.

156
00:07:30,880 --> 00:07:34,360
That smell of a place where many people have passed without leaving a trace.

157
00:07:34,760 --> 00:07:36,860
She sat staring at the tracks for a while,

158
00:07:37,180 --> 00:07:40,140
before taking the black envelope out of the inner pocket of her bag.

159
00:07:40,540 --> 00:07:42,580
The seal gave way with a dry sound.

160
00:07:43,160 --> 00:07:45,240
Inside, three folded sheets.

161
00:07:45,820 --> 00:07:49,220
The first two carried instructions written with almost legal precision.

162
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:51,760
Times, names she should memorize,

163
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:54,220
clothes that would be delivered to the hotel.

164
00:07:54,220 --> 00:07:57,600
What to say if anyone asked how long they had known each other,

165
00:07:57,940 --> 00:08:01,140
Rowine erred them with the same attention she gave to story contracts,

166
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:04,980
mentally noting every detail, every gap between the lines.

167
00:08:05,560 --> 00:08:10,420
The third sheet was smaller, a single line written by hand, unsigned.

168
00:08:10,960 --> 00:08:13,140
Don't smile at anyone like you believe it.

169
00:08:13,420 --> 00:08:14,580
Only smile when I'm looking.

170
00:08:15,080 --> 00:08:16,200
She read it three times.

171
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:17,600
She put it away again.

172
00:08:18,060 --> 00:08:22,060
She looked out the window as the train picked up speed and the city opened into suburb,

173
00:08:22,060 --> 00:08:23,100
then countryside.

174
00:08:23,780 --> 00:08:24,280
There nothing.

175
00:08:24,900 --> 00:08:28,980
And she couldn't decide whether that was an order, a warning, or a request.

176
00:08:29,580 --> 00:08:31,700
The train arrived in Savannah in the late afternoon.

177
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:34,960
The air changed before she even stepped onto the platform.

178
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:37,000
Warmer, denser,

179
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:39,920
laden with a sweet perfume she couldn't yet name.

180
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:41,420
Magnolia maybe.

181
00:08:41,720 --> 00:08:43,500
Or something that grew near water.

182
00:08:43,960 --> 00:08:46,680
Rowine across the station with her folder under her arm,

183
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:49,980
looking for the driver who would be waiting with her name on a sign.

184
00:08:49,980 --> 00:08:55,280
She found the dark car outside, a man in a suit opening the back door without ceremony.

185
00:08:55,880 --> 00:09:00,620
Before getting in, she looked one last time at the city's skyline and saw in the distance.

186
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:05,620
The high roof of the quint mansion cut against the sky that was beginning to turn orange.

187
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:07,680
Too big, too old.

188
00:09:08,140 --> 00:09:10,220
The kind of house that doesn't invite you in.

189
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:11,560
It absorbs you.

190
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:13,360
Rowine sat on the leather seat,

191
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:15,700
rested her head against the cold glass,

192
00:09:16,160 --> 00:09:18,340
and pressed the black envelope against her lap,

193
00:09:18,340 --> 00:09:21,420
like someone clutching a boarding pass to another country.

194
00:09:21,860 --> 00:09:23,800
She took the sheet out one more time.

195
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:25,820
Only smile when I'm looking.

196
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:28,820
She re-read it, folded it, put it away.

197
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:30,500
The car started up,

198
00:09:30,700 --> 00:09:34,560
and the streets of Savannah began to pass by outside like a borrowed set,

199
00:09:34,900 --> 00:09:39,420
with the moss heavy trees and the old houses that each guarded their own version of a secret.

200
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:43,040
And for the first time since Holly's Vaughn had added the word file,

201
00:09:43,700 --> 00:09:44,580
Rowine a pike wondered,

202
00:09:44,580 --> 00:09:48,420
whether she could go home as the same person who had boarded the train.

203
00:09:50,100 --> 00:09:51,700
Chapter 2, a three second kiss.

204
00:09:53,460 --> 00:09:55,740
Who tell sweet was bigger than her entire apartment,

205
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:59,340
with a soft smell of jasmine that seemed built into the walls.

206
00:09:59,980 --> 00:10:02,840
Rowine looked at herself in the oval mirror for a long time,

207
00:10:03,140 --> 00:10:06,760
adjusting the wine-colored silk dress they had left hanging behind the door.

208
00:10:07,140 --> 00:10:08,660
The fabric fell effortlessly.

209
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:13,020
The kind of piece that only existed when someone paid for it without thinking twice.

210
00:10:13,020 --> 00:10:16,740
The driver knocked at the door at the exact time indicated in the envelope.

211
00:10:17,340 --> 00:10:18,240
Rowine went down,

212
00:10:18,540 --> 00:10:21,220
crossed the lobby under stairs she pretended not to notice,

213
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:23,340
and found the car waiting at the curb.

214
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:26,040
The back door opened before she touched the handle,

215
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:30,080
and the first thing she saw inside was the impeccable crease of dark trousers,

216
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:33,000
running down to a pair of polished black shoes.

217
00:10:33,480 --> 00:10:35,780
Jago Quint was seated on the other side of the seat,

218
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:38,340
with one knee slightly apart from the other,

219
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:40,260
hands resting on his own thighs.

220
00:10:40,260 --> 00:10:43,140
He didn't stand, didn't extend his hand.

221
00:10:43,620 --> 00:10:47,080
He merely tilted his chin and inch toward the empty spot beside him,

222
00:10:47,260 --> 00:10:47,760
and waited.

223
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:51,420
Rowine got in, adjusted her skirt with a quick gesture,

224
00:10:52,020 --> 00:10:54,200
and shut the door with more force than necessary.

225
00:10:54,760 --> 00:10:55,260
He noticed.

226
00:10:55,780 --> 00:10:56,900
She saw that he noticed.

227
00:10:57,520 --> 00:10:58,520
Neither of them commented.

228
00:10:59,120 --> 00:11:00,140
Good evening, Miss Pike.

229
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:03,980
His voice was lower than she had imagined from any interview she'd ever read.

230
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:07,000
A voice that didn't rise because it didn't need to.

231
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:10,480
Rowine returned her face and looked at him full on for the first time,

232
00:11:10,900 --> 00:11:14,660
and had the displeasure of confirming that the portraits published over the years did

233
00:11:14,660 --> 00:11:15,460
him no justice.

234
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,940
In person, he was a sculpture of a straight jaw,

235
00:11:19,300 --> 00:11:21,840
dark hair combed back with calculated carelessness,

236
00:11:22,260 --> 00:11:26,580
and eyes that decided the temperature of the room before saying anything at all.

237
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:28,040
Good evening, Mr. Quint.

238
00:11:28,560 --> 00:11:29,520
Jago will do.

239
00:11:29,780 --> 00:11:31,100
Then Rowine will do.

240
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:32,920
He nodded almost imperceptibly,

241
00:11:32,920 --> 00:11:37,140
the car started up, and for a while the two of them sat in silence.

242
00:11:37,780 --> 00:11:39,880
Rowine noticed his hands resting on his knees,

243
00:11:40,380 --> 00:11:43,400
long fingers, a silver watch with no visible brand.

244
00:11:43,880 --> 00:11:47,160
She also noticed that the seat between them held a thin leather folder,

245
00:11:47,420 --> 00:11:50,160
closed, with one corner leaning against the glass.

246
00:11:50,680 --> 00:11:51,200
Details.

247
00:11:51,780 --> 00:11:52,880
She collected details.

248
00:11:53,500 --> 00:11:54,460
Are the rules clear?

249
00:11:54,660 --> 00:11:56,260
He asked without turning his face.

250
00:11:56,740 --> 00:11:56,980
Crystal.

251
00:11:57,560 --> 00:11:58,060
Any questions?

252
00:11:58,760 --> 00:11:59,060
One.

253
00:11:59,700 --> 00:12:02,180
Rowine awaited until he finally turned his gaze to her.

254
00:12:02,180 --> 00:12:04,640
How long do you intend for this night to last?

255
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:07,480
As long as necessary, that's not an answer.

256
00:12:07,940 --> 00:12:09,040
It's the only one I have.

257
00:12:09,380 --> 00:12:13,200
He looked forward again and Rowine accepted defeat in that round without arguing.

258
00:12:13,700 --> 00:12:16,400
She kept watching his profile against the dark window.

259
00:12:16,820 --> 00:12:21,600
The hard line of his jaw, the way his thumb pressed against his own knee in a steady rhythm,

260
00:12:21,980 --> 00:12:24,260
like someone counting something inside himself.

261
00:12:24,620 --> 00:12:27,480
She stored the gesture in her memory, and said nothing.

262
00:12:27,920 --> 00:12:31,120
The Quint mentioned appeared at the end of the avenue of tall trees,

263
00:12:31,120 --> 00:12:33,440
lit from outside like a theatre set.

264
00:12:33,900 --> 00:12:36,100
Rowine drew a deep breath before the car stopped.

265
00:12:36,700 --> 00:12:37,800
Jago got out first.

266
00:12:38,220 --> 00:12:42,480
Went around the vehicle and opened her door with a courtesy that sounded more rehearsed than

267
00:12:42,480 --> 00:12:42,960
sincere.

268
00:12:43,460 --> 00:12:44,500
He offered his arm.

269
00:12:44,900 --> 00:12:45,480
She accepted.

270
00:12:46,040 --> 00:12:49,820
His palm brushed briefly against her hand as he helped her position herself,

271
00:12:50,260 --> 00:12:51,540
and the temperature changed.

272
00:12:52,020 --> 00:12:55,040
Don't smile at anyone like you believe it, he murmured.

273
00:12:55,300 --> 00:12:57,900
Barely moving his lips as they climb the steps.

274
00:12:58,300 --> 00:12:59,860
You already warned me in writing.

275
00:12:59,860 --> 00:13:01,620
I'm reinforcing it.

276
00:13:01,880 --> 00:13:04,200
The main hall swallowed them the moment the door opened.

277
00:13:04,780 --> 00:13:06,680
Rowine has smelled it before she saw anything.

278
00:13:07,340 --> 00:13:08,740
Magnolia and old money.

279
00:13:09,320 --> 00:13:12,040
Exactly as Silas had said in the instruction note.

280
00:13:12,440 --> 00:13:15,460
The white walls rose high to a ceiling of worked stucco,

281
00:13:15,980 --> 00:13:19,920
and everywhere there were antique chandeliers spreading a honey-colored light over the guests.

282
00:13:20,520 --> 00:13:24,660
Long dresses, emerald chocas, men in black tuxedoes,

283
00:13:24,820 --> 00:13:26,300
greeting each other without enthusiasm.

284
00:13:27,100 --> 00:13:29,500
Jago introduced her to three couples in a row,

285
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:31,780
always with the same assembled sentence.

286
00:13:32,380 --> 00:13:34,960
My companion for the evening, Rowine a pike.

287
00:13:35,500 --> 00:13:36,900
No complicated surnames.

288
00:13:37,460 --> 00:13:38,020
No deer.

289
00:13:38,620 --> 00:13:39,140
No love.

290
00:13:39,740 --> 00:13:41,520
Rowine a smile in just the right measure.

291
00:13:42,140 --> 00:13:44,140
Answered questions in just the right measure.

292
00:13:44,680 --> 00:13:45,600
And noticed everything.

293
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:48,080
She noticed that he avoided the terrace.

294
00:13:48,560 --> 00:13:51,900
Twice a waiter passed offering to take guests out to the outdoor area.

295
00:13:52,300 --> 00:13:53,780
And both times Jago declined,

296
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:56,020
with a minimal gesture of his chin,

297
00:13:56,560 --> 00:13:58,120
without even looking at the glass door.

298
00:13:58,120 --> 00:14:01,440
She also noticed that his gaze had one point,

299
00:14:01,860 --> 00:14:03,680
tripped over an empty chair near the window.

300
00:14:04,220 --> 00:14:06,100
A chair upholstered in dark green velvet,

301
00:14:06,620 --> 00:14:08,500
slightly set apart from the rest of the arrangement,

302
00:14:09,100 --> 00:14:12,340
as if it belonged to someone who used to sit there and hadn't arrived yet.

303
00:14:12,640 --> 00:14:13,580
He looked away quickly.

304
00:14:14,380 --> 00:14:14,900
Rowineerstorted.

305
00:14:15,460 --> 00:14:16,600
What an unlikely evening.

306
00:14:17,080 --> 00:14:20,120
The voice came from behind her sweetest syrup heated too much.

307
00:14:20,640 --> 00:14:23,920
Rowine returned and found a woman with red hair pinned in a low bun,

308
00:14:24,380 --> 00:14:25,820
an emerald green dress,

309
00:14:25,820 --> 00:14:27,880
a smile that didn't reach her eyes.

310
00:14:28,460 --> 00:14:30,200
Jago stiffened beside her.

311
00:14:30,420 --> 00:14:32,460
Odeit, he greeted her without warmth.

312
00:14:32,960 --> 00:14:33,380
Jago.

313
00:14:34,060 --> 00:14:35,980
Odeitmachand extended her hand to Rowine,

314
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:37,080
palm down,

315
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:39,640
the gesture of someone expecting reverence,

316
00:14:40,160 --> 00:14:40,980
and the companion.

317
00:14:41,560 --> 00:14:42,120
How interesting.

318
00:14:42,760 --> 00:14:43,580
What do you do, dear?

319
00:14:44,160 --> 00:14:44,680
I write.

320
00:14:45,340 --> 00:14:45,540
Ah.

321
00:14:46,040 --> 00:14:48,120
Odeit seemed to decide something in silence.

322
00:14:48,680 --> 00:14:50,500
How brave of him to bring you here.

323
00:14:50,880 --> 00:14:52,420
Brave of me to agree to come.

324
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:53,700
Odeit laughed.

325
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:56,320
A short note that contained nothing of laughter.

326
00:14:56,780 --> 00:14:58,780
Then she moved off with a wave of her fingers,

327
00:14:59,340 --> 00:15:01,560
leaving behind a trail of expensive perfume.

328
00:15:02,140 --> 00:15:05,200
Jago rested his hand at the small of Rowine's back

329
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:06,400
for just a second,

330
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:09,140
a gesture of ownership that wasn't affection.

331
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:10,800
Then he withdrew it.

332
00:15:11,020 --> 00:15:12,520
You didn't need to provoke her.

333
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:13,420
He remarked.

334
00:15:13,660 --> 00:15:13,860
Low.

335
00:15:14,460 --> 00:15:15,460
I did, actually.

336
00:15:16,100 --> 00:15:16,720
He didn't answer.

337
00:15:17,120 --> 00:15:18,960
But the corner of his mouth moved a millimeter,

338
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:22,360
and Rowine arrested it as if it were the headline of the month.

339
00:15:22,360 --> 00:15:24,160
It wasn't a smile yet.

340
00:15:24,520 --> 00:15:25,360
It was close.

341
00:15:26,020 --> 00:15:28,260
The silence in the hall changed texture

342
00:15:28,260 --> 00:15:30,200
before she understood why.

343
00:15:30,540 --> 00:15:33,060
It was as if the air had drawn back a few inches,

344
00:15:33,520 --> 00:15:37,400
and everybody there in Unison had turned their heads in the same direction.

345
00:15:38,100 --> 00:15:39,720
Rowine followed the others gaze,

346
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:42,880
and saw you door a quint entering through the main door.

347
00:15:43,280 --> 00:15:45,420
The matriarch didn't need to announce herself.

348
00:15:45,680 --> 00:15:49,820
A long black dress, a pearl necklace that fell to the middle of her chest,

349
00:15:49,820 --> 00:15:53,040
gray hair pinned with a rigidity that allowed no discussion.

350
00:15:53,660 --> 00:15:55,360
She crossed the hall without greeting anyone,

351
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:57,820
and stopped before her son and his companion,

352
00:15:58,300 --> 00:16:00,640
with the expression of someone appraising merchandise.

353
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:03,160
Good evening, mother, said Jago.

354
00:16:03,720 --> 00:16:05,360
You'dora didn't answer her son.

355
00:16:05,740 --> 00:16:07,360
She turned her pale eyes to Rowina,

356
00:16:07,860 --> 00:16:09,900
and examined her from shoes to hairstyle,

357
00:16:10,500 --> 00:16:11,760
with a surgical calm.

358
00:16:12,240 --> 00:16:13,900
Then she stepped half a step closer,

359
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:16,200
and the voice that came out of her was low,

360
00:16:16,300 --> 00:16:18,140
but sharp enough to cut the entire hall.

361
00:16:18,140 --> 00:16:20,460
I don't see love here, my son.

362
00:16:20,920 --> 00:16:23,120
The silence closed around the three of them.

363
00:16:23,520 --> 00:16:26,100
Rowina felt Jago's body stiffened beside her,

364
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:28,040
his shoulders rising half an inch.

365
00:16:28,520 --> 00:16:30,840
Yudora stayed put, chin raised waiting.

366
00:16:31,420 --> 00:16:32,840
Proof said the matriarch.

367
00:16:33,340 --> 00:16:35,060
If it's true, prove it.

368
00:16:35,280 --> 00:16:38,780
The entire hall turned, heads lifted from champagne glasses,

369
00:16:39,360 --> 00:16:40,260
conversations ceased,

370
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:42,200
waiters stopped where they stood.

371
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:46,500
Rowina felt the weight of the whole hall falling on her and Jago at the same time.

372
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:47,680
He locked up.

373
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:49,160
She saw that he locked up.

374
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:51,420
His thumb stopped counting on his own hip,

375
00:16:51,700 --> 00:16:52,700
his jaw hardened,

376
00:16:53,140 --> 00:16:56,200
and for a whole second, no decision came out of his body.

377
00:16:56,680 --> 00:16:57,960
Rowina decided for him.

378
00:16:58,180 --> 00:17:00,920
She raised her hand took his face by the side and pulled.

379
00:17:01,380 --> 00:17:05,160
His mouth met hers with a hesitation of someone who hadn't rehearsed this scene,

380
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:08,200
and for an instant, Rowina thought he wouldn't respond.

381
00:17:08,840 --> 00:17:10,180
Then his breath faltered.

382
00:17:10,640 --> 00:17:11,620
She felt the falter,

383
00:17:12,020 --> 00:17:13,940
felt the air caught halfway up his chest,

384
00:17:13,940 --> 00:17:18,360
felt his hand rise by reflex to her back and settle between her shoulder blades,

385
00:17:18,900 --> 00:17:21,080
with a pressure that didn't belong to the charade.

386
00:17:21,580 --> 00:17:23,540
The kiss was supposed to last a second.

387
00:17:24,040 --> 00:17:25,160
It lasted three.

388
00:17:25,540 --> 00:17:26,220
Maybe more.

389
00:17:26,840 --> 00:17:30,680
Rowina lost count somewhere between the moment he tilted his head a little to the side,

390
00:17:31,140 --> 00:17:34,420
and the moment she herself forgot there was a hall around them.

391
00:17:34,620 --> 00:17:37,440
When they pulled apart, she opened her eyes first.

392
00:17:37,860 --> 00:17:39,220
He took half a second longer,

393
00:17:39,580 --> 00:17:42,480
and what Rowina saw on his face when he finally looked back,

394
00:17:42,480 --> 00:17:44,560
was the same thing she felt inside,

395
00:17:45,040 --> 00:17:46,980
and which she wasn't prepared to name yet.

396
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:49,240
Udora stepped back half a step.

397
00:17:49,580 --> 00:17:52,580
She adjusted her pearl necklace with a calculated carelessness,

398
00:17:53,120 --> 00:17:57,080
and the corner of her mouth drew a line that wasn't a smile but pretended to be.

399
00:17:57,260 --> 00:17:57,480
Good.

400
00:17:58,040 --> 00:17:58,980
Mermaid the matriarch.

401
00:17:59,440 --> 00:18:01,060
I hope to see you again many times.

402
00:18:01,660 --> 00:18:01,900
Many.

403
00:18:02,460 --> 00:18:04,260
She turned on her heels and moved off.

404
00:18:04,600 --> 00:18:06,960
The hall little by little began to breathe again.

405
00:18:07,680 --> 00:18:10,000
Conversations returned like a discreet murmur.

406
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:11,060
Waters moved.

407
00:18:11,580 --> 00:18:14,260
Someone laughed in the distance at something that wasn't funny.

408
00:18:14,820 --> 00:18:16,300
Rowina kept looking at Jago.

409
00:18:16,760 --> 00:18:19,140
His hand was still on her back forgotten there,

410
00:18:19,260 --> 00:18:20,440
in no hurry to leave.

411
00:18:20,840 --> 00:18:22,540
He took his time pulling it back.

412
00:18:22,860 --> 00:18:26,220
When he did, his fingers passed slowly over the silk of the dress,

413
00:18:26,360 --> 00:18:29,580
like someone memorizing a path they might need to retrace later.

414
00:18:29,880 --> 00:18:32,960
Across the hall Odec-Marshon watched them with a glass in her hand,

415
00:18:33,300 --> 00:18:35,200
and her smile was now a different one.

416
00:18:35,580 --> 00:18:37,040
Rowina registered it.

417
00:18:37,040 --> 00:18:40,200
She already knew, without needing a warning,

418
00:18:40,740 --> 00:18:42,340
that that woman would want payback.

419
00:18:42,720 --> 00:18:44,240
Jago leaned in very slightly,

420
00:18:44,760 --> 00:18:47,600
and spoke close to her ear so low that only she could hear.

421
00:18:47,900 --> 00:18:49,060
You owe me an explanation.

422
00:18:49,740 --> 00:18:50,520
For the kiss?

423
00:18:50,980 --> 00:18:52,040
For the length of the kiss.

424
00:18:52,660 --> 00:18:53,620
Rowina didn't answer.

425
00:18:54,060 --> 00:18:55,420
She didn't know the answer yet.

426
00:18:55,680 --> 00:18:56,940
She took the glass away to her,

427
00:18:57,220 --> 00:18:59,680
drank a sip she didn't even feel go down,

428
00:19:00,140 --> 00:19:02,420
and looked again at the empty chair near the window.

429
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:05,820
Someone, at some point, had sat in it.

430
00:19:05,820 --> 00:19:07,980
Someone who now was no longer there,

431
00:19:08,340 --> 00:19:11,860
and Rowina Pike, who had collected details since childhood,

432
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:14,900
understood that the most important story of that night,

433
00:19:15,280 --> 00:19:18,570
had nothing to do with the reason Hollis Vaughan had sent her there.

434
00:19:20,420 --> 00:19:22,920
Chapter 3, Coffee with No Recorder.

435
00:19:24,280 --> 00:19:26,340
The morning after the ball arrived without ceremony,

436
00:19:26,940 --> 00:19:29,960
the Savannah Sun came through the gaps in the curtain of the guest room,

437
00:19:30,320 --> 00:19:33,220
at the Quint Mansion with an almost impolite insistence,

438
00:19:33,220 --> 00:19:37,980
and Rowina Pike opened her eyes before she remembered exactly where she was.

439
00:19:38,340 --> 00:19:40,340
It took a whole instant for the high ceiling,

440
00:19:40,920 --> 00:19:45,440
the carved footboard, and the thick silence of the house to organize themselves in her head.

441
00:19:45,840 --> 00:19:47,640
Only then did the kiss come back.

442
00:19:47,920 --> 00:19:49,760
It came back first through her lip.

443
00:19:50,200 --> 00:19:51,640
Then through the nape of her neck,

444
00:19:52,100 --> 00:19:52,920
then through her stomach.

445
00:19:53,340 --> 00:19:55,840
Three seconds that now carried the weight of biography.

446
00:19:56,460 --> 00:19:59,000
She sat on the edge of the bed and looked at her own hands.

447
00:19:59,440 --> 00:20:00,200
They were cold.

448
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:03,560
Someone had left a coffee tray on the sideboard beside the door,

449
00:20:03,940 --> 00:20:05,020
during the night probably,

450
00:20:05,580 --> 00:20:07,200
because the cup was no longer steaming.

451
00:20:07,760 --> 00:20:12,200
Beside it a short note, written by hand in a hand writing she recognized at once,

452
00:20:12,660 --> 00:20:14,120
garden, whenever you can.

453
00:20:14,580 --> 00:20:19,180
Jay Rowina re-read the note twice just to prove to herself that it hadn't unsettled her.

454
00:20:19,380 --> 00:20:20,100
It didn't stick.

455
00:20:20,460 --> 00:20:23,720
The garden was at the back of the house, far from the main hall.

456
00:20:24,080 --> 00:20:26,600
She noticed that as a small paleide housekeeper,

457
00:20:27,040 --> 00:20:28,620
let her down a corridor of portraits.

458
00:20:28,620 --> 00:20:31,380
The woman introduced herself as neve,

459
00:20:31,780 --> 00:20:33,580
lightly squeezed Rowina's arm and said,

460
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:35,540
in an accent from rural Georgia,

461
00:20:36,060 --> 00:20:37,660
that Mr. Jego was already waiting.

462
00:20:38,240 --> 00:20:40,360
There was warmth in her voice but also scrutiny.

463
00:20:41,260 --> 00:20:44,100
Rowina smiled with her mouth closed and asked nothing.

464
00:20:44,640 --> 00:20:48,060
Jego Quint was standing near an old rose bush with his back to the house.

465
00:20:48,560 --> 00:20:50,520
White shirt sleeves folded to the elbow,

466
00:20:51,100 --> 00:20:52,340
hair still wet from his shower.

467
00:20:52,860 --> 00:20:54,900
He turned when he heard the gravel and for a second,

468
00:20:54,900 --> 00:20:58,360
just one, his eyes met hers unguarded,

469
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:00,920
without their usual controlled gleam.

470
00:21:01,460 --> 00:21:03,120
Then his jaw firmed up again.

471
00:21:03,560 --> 00:21:04,160
Did you sleep?

472
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:06,300
As much as I could, she answered,

473
00:21:06,820 --> 00:21:07,840
the house makes noises.

474
00:21:08,420 --> 00:21:11,760
It does. He pointed with his chin toward a cast iron bench.

475
00:21:12,340 --> 00:21:13,000
Sit with me.

476
00:21:13,260 --> 00:21:15,220
We need to work out what comes next.

477
00:21:15,760 --> 00:21:19,520
Rowina obeyed, but chose to sit in profile knees turned outward.

478
00:21:19,980 --> 00:21:21,420
A small defense he noticed.

479
00:21:21,960 --> 00:21:22,700
He said nothing.

480
00:21:22,700 --> 00:21:25,100
You have the interview, Jego began,

481
00:21:25,560 --> 00:21:28,040
his voice low and chosen word by word.

482
00:21:28,520 --> 00:21:29,440
That's still standing,

483
00:21:29,960 --> 00:21:32,160
but last night raised an issue I didn't foresee.

484
00:21:32,720 --> 00:21:34,720
My mother didn't believe it until the kiss.

485
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:36,440
Maybe she believed it afterward.

486
00:21:36,980 --> 00:21:38,180
If you disappear tomorrow,

487
00:21:38,680 --> 00:21:40,040
she'll get suspicious again.

488
00:21:40,400 --> 00:21:42,820
And I'll have three candidates on the table by Sunday.

489
00:21:43,240 --> 00:21:44,720
You're asking me for more days.

490
00:21:45,120 --> 00:21:46,240
I'm asking for weeks.

491
00:21:46,840 --> 00:21:50,620
Rowina swallowed the small shock and breathed through her mouth before answering.

492
00:21:50,620 --> 00:21:51,940
Weeks of what?

493
00:21:52,480 --> 00:21:53,040
Appearances.

494
00:21:53,600 --> 00:21:55,080
A dinner here and event there.

495
00:21:55,440 --> 00:21:58,860
Enough for Savannah to believe you're the woman who finally got into this house.

496
00:21:59,140 --> 00:21:59,700
He paused.

497
00:22:00,240 --> 00:22:01,700
Same payment, same interview.

498
00:22:02,240 --> 00:22:03,120
Just a longer timeline.

499
00:22:03,720 --> 00:22:05,040
There was logic in the proposal.

500
00:22:05,560 --> 00:22:06,460
And there was a trap.

501
00:22:06,760 --> 00:22:07,600
She knew both.

502
00:22:07,900 --> 00:22:08,800
And if I refuse,

503
00:22:09,380 --> 00:22:10,660
you get the interview anyway.

504
00:22:10,920 --> 00:22:12,040
He said without hesitating.

505
00:22:12,620 --> 00:22:15,400
We agreed on something and I don't undo what's agreed.

506
00:22:15,980 --> 00:22:17,660
That was what disarmed her.

507
00:22:17,860 --> 00:22:18,680
Not the proposal.

508
00:22:18,680 --> 00:22:20,660
The resolution of the proposal.

509
00:22:21,280 --> 00:22:22,860
Rowina bit the inside of her cheek.

510
00:22:23,320 --> 00:22:26,040
Looked at the nearest rose counted to three and said yes.

511
00:22:26,520 --> 00:22:27,240
He didn't smile.

512
00:22:27,660 --> 00:22:30,660
He just nodded slightly, like someone closing her claws.

513
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:33,440
But when she stood up to go back into the house,

514
00:22:33,660 --> 00:22:35,880
his hand brushed her back for half a second,

515
00:22:36,320 --> 00:22:37,980
had a spot below her shoulder blade.

516
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:41,180
And lingered an instant longer than any contract required.

517
00:22:41,640 --> 00:22:43,620
She stored the gesture alongside the others.

518
00:22:43,860 --> 00:22:44,940
She was already collecting.

519
00:22:45,540 --> 00:22:47,200
The following weeks arrived slowly,

520
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:48,680
and without a truce.

521
00:22:49,220 --> 00:22:51,480
Rowina began to split herself between the newsroom

522
00:22:51,480 --> 00:22:54,900
where Marlo covered her shifts with increasingly irritated humour,

523
00:22:55,340 --> 00:22:56,460
and the streets of Savannah,

524
00:22:57,000 --> 00:22:59,820
where she learned there were neighborhoods where the air smelled of wet

525
00:22:59,820 --> 00:23:03,060
Jasmine and others where it only smelled of hoarded money.

526
00:23:03,500 --> 00:23:05,240
Jego always sent for her at the station,

527
00:23:05,680 --> 00:23:07,940
with the same driver and always in the same car.

528
00:23:08,380 --> 00:23:10,820
He waited for her inside, in the back seat,

529
00:23:11,260 --> 00:23:13,040
shoulder leaning against the opposite door.

530
00:23:13,520 --> 00:23:17,140
One Tuesday, he took her to an antique's fair under the oaks of the old

531
00:23:17,860 --> 00:23:20,360
Rowina stopped in front of a tray of loose pendants,

532
00:23:20,800 --> 00:23:22,820
and picked up one shaped like a crooked owl.

533
00:23:23,380 --> 00:23:26,480
Half green with age, set with ridiculous red stones.

534
00:23:27,020 --> 00:23:30,940
It's ugly, she said, smiling at the object as if it were an accomplice.

535
00:23:31,480 --> 00:23:32,840
It is, Jego agreed.

536
00:23:33,320 --> 00:23:35,000
She put the pendant back on the tray.

537
00:23:35,420 --> 00:23:36,580
She didn't ask for it.

538
00:23:36,780 --> 00:23:37,380
Didn't haggle.

539
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:38,640
Didn't look at it again.

540
00:23:39,220 --> 00:23:41,960
Half an hour later, when they were heading back to the car,

541
00:23:42,420 --> 00:23:45,560
he passed the dark velvet box into her hand without any ceremony,

542
00:23:45,560 --> 00:23:48,120
and Rowina stood in the middle of the sidewalk,

543
00:23:48,560 --> 00:23:51,320
holding the crooked owl as if it were a live animal.

544
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:53,520
You didn't haggle, she remarked.

545
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:56,300
No, he opened the car door for her.

546
00:23:56,460 --> 00:23:57,940
I knew what it was worth to you.

547
00:23:58,180 --> 00:24:01,900
It was that day that Rowina didn't turn on the recorder for the entire afternoon.

548
00:24:02,460 --> 00:24:07,100
She sat with Jego in his office on the 13th floor of a glass building in downtown savanna,

549
00:24:07,560 --> 00:24:10,300
and they talked about things no interview called for.

550
00:24:10,540 --> 00:24:12,160
A cousin he had never saw.

551
00:24:12,580 --> 00:24:14,780
A book she had read 12 times in her teams.

552
00:24:14,780 --> 00:24:17,840
A specific smell of the coffee her mother used to make.

553
00:24:18,200 --> 00:24:21,900
Jego poured her coffee that afternoon in a way she hadn't taught him.

554
00:24:22,120 --> 00:24:24,240
Half a spoon of sugar, a splash of milk.

555
00:24:24,740 --> 00:24:25,360
Very hot.

556
00:24:25,960 --> 00:24:29,920
Rowina looked at the cup, looked at him, and didn't ask how he knew.

557
00:24:30,320 --> 00:24:33,760
Neeve let the answer slip a week later in the mansions kitchen,

558
00:24:34,280 --> 00:24:38,900
while drying a crystal glass with the attention of someone handling something bigger than a glass.

559
00:24:39,380 --> 00:24:41,380
He's been sleeping better since you've been coming.

560
00:24:41,920 --> 00:24:44,420
The housekeeper didn't look at Rowina as she said it.

561
00:24:44,420 --> 00:24:47,100
It's not a compliment, it's an observation.

562
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:50,660
Rowina laughed softly without breath to answer.

563
00:24:51,100 --> 00:24:52,820
Do you want to know something miss?

564
00:24:53,220 --> 00:24:55,320
Neeve continued, putting the glass away.

565
00:24:55,760 --> 00:24:58,700
It's been a long time since anyone asked him how his day was.

566
00:24:59,060 --> 00:25:02,280
He would be grateful, even if he didn't know how to thank you.

567
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:05,240
Rowina's hand trembled slightly on the handle of her mug.

568
00:25:05,580 --> 00:25:08,060
She set the mug down on the marble with doubled care.

569
00:25:08,520 --> 00:25:10,380
The charity event took place on a Thursday.

570
00:25:10,380 --> 00:25:14,840
It was an auction in aid of a children's hospital in a vaulted ceiling tall,

571
00:25:15,140 --> 00:25:18,460
where the candleabras seemed too heavy for the wire that held them.

572
00:25:18,900 --> 00:25:21,620
Rowina wore a dark green dress borrowed from Marlo's sister,

573
00:25:22,060 --> 00:25:26,880
and Jago appeared at her side at the entrance, as if he'd matched the exact time to his own watch.

574
00:25:27,420 --> 00:25:29,740
Odec Marshaar arrived 20 minutes later.

575
00:25:30,180 --> 00:25:32,440
Rowina saw her approach from the other side of the hall,

576
00:25:32,760 --> 00:25:34,280
greeting people with thin kisses.

577
00:25:34,820 --> 00:25:37,280
A champagne coloured dress moving like liquid.

578
00:25:37,280 --> 00:25:42,740
Odec stopped in front of Rowina, looked her up and down with a smile too polite to be polite,

579
00:25:43,220 --> 00:25:46,100
and said in a tone that carried through the three nearest people,

580
00:25:46,560 --> 00:25:47,480
you hold up well dear.

581
00:25:47,960 --> 00:25:51,060
A borrowed dress in a hall of this caliber isn't for just anyone.

582
00:25:51,460 --> 00:25:53,140
I hope the night is kind to you.

583
00:25:53,420 --> 00:25:55,220
The air in the hall became specific.

584
00:25:55,700 --> 00:25:57,680
Two women near the buffet stopped chewing.

585
00:25:58,340 --> 00:26:02,380
Rowina felt the blood rise up her neck and choose between turning into fury

586
00:26:02,380 --> 00:26:04,000
and turning into dignity.

587
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:08,360
Before she could decide, Jago's hand touched the small of her back.

588
00:26:08,780 --> 00:26:12,120
Firm, without theatrical possession, just presence,

589
00:26:12,700 --> 00:26:15,960
and he took half a step forward, shoulder pressed against hers.

590
00:26:16,300 --> 00:26:20,140
Odec, he said, and his voice was no longer lower than usual,

591
00:26:20,720 --> 00:26:22,200
only stripped of anything amiable.

592
00:26:22,620 --> 00:26:26,700
If you have any doubts about the woman I came with, put those doubts to me directly.

593
00:26:27,320 --> 00:26:30,400
Rowina owes you no explanation about where she buys any dress.

594
00:26:30,740 --> 00:26:31,400
Neither do you.

595
00:26:31,400 --> 00:26:36,560
Odec parted her lips, and something inside her smile gave way for half a second,

596
00:26:37,020 --> 00:26:37,960
before recomposing.

597
00:26:38,460 --> 00:26:40,200
Now touchy Jago, it was a compliment.

598
00:26:40,660 --> 00:26:41,200
It wasn't.

599
00:26:41,660 --> 00:26:44,060
He didn't raise his tone, he didn't need to.

600
00:26:44,340 --> 00:26:48,040
Two people nearby rediscovered a sudden fascination with their own shoes.

601
00:26:48,560 --> 00:26:52,460
Odec nodded, murmured a phrase about finding a friend and with Drew.

602
00:26:52,860 --> 00:26:56,120
Jago didn't move his hand from Rowina's back for a few more seconds,

603
00:26:56,580 --> 00:26:58,420
and in those seconds she felt everything.

604
00:26:58,420 --> 00:27:03,180
His thumb resting exactly on the seam of her dress, the heat of his palm,

605
00:27:03,640 --> 00:27:06,880
the silent weight of being chosen there before an entire room.

606
00:27:07,280 --> 00:27:09,200
When he moved his hand away, it was slow.

607
00:27:09,820 --> 00:27:10,860
Rowina drew a breath.

608
00:27:11,220 --> 00:27:12,240
You didn't need to.

609
00:27:12,600 --> 00:27:15,780
I did, actually, he answered, without looking at her.

610
00:27:16,020 --> 00:27:17,400
She knew what she was doing.

611
00:27:17,900 --> 00:27:19,660
The rest of the night passed in waves.

612
00:27:20,180 --> 00:27:24,660
Rowina won a small lot with the money she had, a pair of glass earrings no-one wanted.

613
00:27:25,260 --> 00:27:26,300
Jago won nothing.

614
00:27:26,300 --> 00:27:29,580
He just watched her from afar, from across the hall,

615
00:27:30,000 --> 00:27:33,020
and every time she raised her eyes, he was already looking.

616
00:27:33,520 --> 00:27:35,480
They returned to the mansion around midnight.

617
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:40,480
She went up to the guest room and stood for a long time in front of the open suitcase on the floor,

618
00:27:40,900 --> 00:27:45,480
at the bottom of it, under two folded blouses, and a pair of old shoes.

619
00:27:46,020 --> 00:27:46,680
Was the file.

620
00:27:47,220 --> 00:27:50,300
Brown, no label, tied with a rubber band.

621
00:27:50,720 --> 00:27:54,120
Rowina pulled it into her lap, sat on the rug and stayed looking.

622
00:27:54,480 --> 00:27:55,540
She didn't open it.

623
00:27:55,540 --> 00:27:58,720
She ran her thumb along the edge, drew a deep breath,

624
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:01,080
and returned the file to the bottom of the suitcase.

625
00:28:01,700 --> 00:28:06,580
She folded the blouses over it with exaggerated care, as if covering it were enough to undo

626
00:28:06,580 --> 00:28:07,460
what labour-neath.

627
00:28:07,900 --> 00:28:09,660
A phone on the nightstand vibrated.

628
00:28:10,280 --> 00:28:11,560
Rowina glanced sideways.

629
00:28:12,240 --> 00:28:13,020
A missed call.

630
00:28:13,520 --> 00:28:13,960
Then another.

631
00:28:14,340 --> 00:28:15,880
Then a third one she watched arrive.

632
00:28:16,400 --> 00:28:19,420
Pollis Vaughan's name blinking on the screen like a silent alarm.

633
00:28:19,760 --> 00:28:21,280
She let it ring until it stopped.

634
00:28:21,720 --> 00:28:24,160
She kept looking at the phone until the light went out.

635
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:28,300
When she lowered her head again, the phone vibrated a fourth time.

636
00:28:28,840 --> 00:28:29,360
A fifth.

637
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:31,120
Rowina closed her eyes.

638
00:28:31,600 --> 00:28:34,100
Across the corridor, someone walked slowly.

639
00:28:34,700 --> 00:28:35,920
Bear feet on the wood.

640
00:28:36,360 --> 00:28:39,400
She knew who steps they were, and she didn't open the door.

641
00:28:39,760 --> 00:28:40,520
The phone kept.

642
00:28:41,900 --> 00:28:43,880
Chapter 4 The File She Wouldn't Open.

643
00:28:45,340 --> 00:28:45,540
ringing.

644
00:28:46,080 --> 00:28:48,760
Pollis Vaughan's fifth call came just after dawn.

645
00:28:49,200 --> 00:28:51,040
And this time, Rowina answered.

646
00:28:51,560 --> 00:28:53,340
She was sitting on the floor of the guest room,

647
00:28:53,340 --> 00:28:55,440
still in the wrinkled green dress.

648
00:28:55,780 --> 00:28:57,240
The glass earrings in her lap.

649
00:28:57,560 --> 00:29:00,240
The phone trembling in her hand for the sixth time.

650
00:29:00,700 --> 00:29:02,720
The rug beneath her smelled of old lavender.

651
00:29:03,380 --> 00:29:05,260
The kind of lavender that isn't perfume.

652
00:29:05,880 --> 00:29:06,540
It's time.

653
00:29:07,060 --> 00:29:09,240
You vanished, said Hollis without a greeting.

654
00:29:09,820 --> 00:29:12,940
His voice had that measured calm that preceded fireings.

655
00:29:13,260 --> 00:29:14,860
I haven't heard your voice in three weeks.

656
00:29:15,380 --> 00:29:16,620
Don't give me behind schedule.

657
00:29:17,120 --> 00:29:18,160
It's behind schedule.

658
00:29:18,440 --> 00:29:19,300
That's not the point.

659
00:29:19,820 --> 00:29:20,900
The point is the material.

660
00:29:21,400 --> 00:29:22,100
Where is it?

661
00:29:22,320 --> 00:29:22,780
I'm working.

662
00:29:22,780 --> 00:29:23,860
You're not.

663
00:29:24,320 --> 00:29:27,020
Rowina closed her eyes and rested her forehead on her knee.

664
00:29:27,440 --> 00:29:29,640
The knee was cold through the wrinkled fabric.

665
00:29:30,120 --> 00:29:32,400
Outside the garden hadn't quite woken up yet.

666
00:29:32,760 --> 00:29:35,180
A shallow grey light spread across the window,

667
00:29:35,640 --> 00:29:38,020
as if the day was still convincing itself to arrive.

668
00:29:38,540 --> 00:29:38,840
Pollis.

669
00:29:39,520 --> 00:29:39,860
Rowina.

670
00:29:40,400 --> 00:29:42,260
He drew a deep breath on the other end of the line.

671
00:29:42,760 --> 00:29:43,600
I backed you.

672
00:29:43,920 --> 00:29:44,600
I bought the ticket.

673
00:29:45,160 --> 00:29:49,060
Paid for the hotel the first weekend, kept your shift going with Marlo covering three

674
00:29:49,060 --> 00:29:49,740
straight shifts.

675
00:29:50,200 --> 00:29:51,180
I'm not a benefactor.

676
00:29:51,460 --> 00:29:52,020
I'm an editor.

677
00:29:52,020 --> 00:29:54,020
And an editor needs to deliver.

678
00:29:54,580 --> 00:29:57,620
Either you send me something by Monday night or I'll have to make a decision

679
00:29:57,620 --> 00:29:58,680
neither of us once.

680
00:29:59,100 --> 00:30:00,380
She didn't answer right away.

681
00:30:00,880 --> 00:30:04,640
Outside, a bird insisted on the same short note near the window.

682
00:30:05,220 --> 00:30:09,000
And Rowina caught herself thinking about how Jago used to be late with the coffee,

683
00:30:09,560 --> 00:30:10,880
whenever there was a bird nearby.

684
00:30:11,420 --> 00:30:13,080
He'd stand out on the porch for a moment,

685
00:30:13,560 --> 00:30:15,860
listening, the cup forgotten in his hand.

686
00:30:16,280 --> 00:30:17,760
She shouldn't have noticed that.

687
00:30:18,040 --> 00:30:18,860
She had noticed.

688
00:30:19,400 --> 00:30:20,260
I heard you.

689
00:30:20,480 --> 00:30:21,200
She said finally.

690
00:30:21,200 --> 00:30:22,460
You didn't.

691
00:30:22,640 --> 00:30:23,180
Hollis answered.

692
00:30:23,760 --> 00:30:24,520
But you will.

693
00:30:24,900 --> 00:30:26,940
Monday night, headline or resignation.

694
00:30:27,680 --> 00:30:28,520
He hung up first.

695
00:30:29,060 --> 00:30:32,220
Rowina kept looking at the phone for a length of time she couldn't measure.

696
00:30:32,640 --> 00:30:35,720
The reflection of her own distorted face on the black screen.

697
00:30:36,180 --> 00:30:37,240
She stood up slowly.

698
00:30:37,740 --> 00:30:41,420
She walked to the suitcase which was half open on a wooden chair near the dresser.

699
00:30:41,580 --> 00:30:45,580
She pulled the brown file out by the rubber band, sat down again on the rug,

700
00:30:45,980 --> 00:30:47,840
and rested the file on her own thighs.

701
00:30:48,380 --> 00:30:49,840
Her hands were still this time.

702
00:30:49,840 --> 00:30:51,460
Stiller than she expected.

703
00:30:52,040 --> 00:30:53,880
She untied the rubber band slowly.

704
00:30:54,460 --> 00:30:55,640
She opened the first flap.

705
00:30:57,260 --> 00:30:58,720
Clippings of balance sheets.

706
00:30:59,300 --> 00:31:02,080
Photocopies Hollis had obtained from some discrete source.

707
00:31:02,460 --> 00:31:06,460
Notes in small handwriting written by herself before she met Jago Quint.

708
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:09,700
In a gray, noisy newsroom where the coffee was bad,

709
00:31:10,060 --> 00:31:12,260
and ambition still seemed enough to pay the bills.

710
00:31:12,820 --> 00:31:15,140
Rowina read two lines of her own field notebook,

711
00:31:15,580 --> 00:31:17,920
and didn't recognize the woman who had written that.

712
00:31:18,120 --> 00:31:19,100
She closed the file.

713
00:31:19,100 --> 00:31:21,040
She tied the rubber band again.

714
00:31:21,460 --> 00:31:23,480
She put everything back at the bottom of the suitcase.

715
00:31:24,200 --> 00:31:26,820
The partner's dinner was scheduled for that same night.

716
00:31:27,300 --> 00:31:31,260
Neve came up in the late afternoon with a dress hanging from a velvet hanger.

717
00:31:31,840 --> 00:31:35,120
Deep wine, straight neckline, sleeves to the elbow.

718
00:31:35,600 --> 00:31:37,820
The fabric had a specific weight to the touch,

719
00:31:38,240 --> 00:31:40,300
that weight of something chosen with attention.

720
00:31:40,880 --> 00:31:42,560
Rowina looked at her without understanding.

721
00:31:43,180 --> 00:31:47,260
From the master said Neve and set the hanger on the chair against the wall,

722
00:31:47,260 --> 00:31:49,040
he asked me to leave it here.

723
00:31:49,300 --> 00:31:51,600
He said the miss isn't obliged to wear it.

724
00:31:51,940 --> 00:31:53,760
Rowina laughed without joy,

725
00:31:54,160 --> 00:31:55,420
and if I don't wear it.

726
00:31:55,640 --> 00:31:57,400
He won't ask why, said Neve,

727
00:31:57,800 --> 00:32:00,200
with a half smile that didn't quite complete itself.

728
00:32:00,600 --> 00:32:01,300
But he'll notice.

729
00:32:01,820 --> 00:32:02,360
He notices.

730
00:32:02,960 --> 00:32:03,940
She wore the dress.

731
00:32:04,380 --> 00:32:06,960
She couldn't decide whether it was surrender or courage,

732
00:32:07,300 --> 00:32:08,880
and she chose not to decide.

733
00:32:09,380 --> 00:32:11,320
The mansion's dining room had 18 places,

734
00:32:11,880 --> 00:32:14,100
and a table that was a vanished skating rink.

735
00:32:14,540 --> 00:32:16,280
There were six partners, three wives,

736
00:32:16,280 --> 00:32:19,480
Silas Ashford at one end in the same gray suit as always,

737
00:32:19,860 --> 00:32:22,680
and the face of someone who has already seen far too much,

738
00:32:22,960 --> 00:32:24,460
without being surprised by anything,

739
00:32:25,040 --> 00:32:26,780
and you door a quint at the other end,

740
00:32:27,280 --> 00:32:29,580
seated as though the seat had been built around her.

741
00:32:29,980 --> 00:32:31,360
Rowina entered beside Jego.

742
00:32:31,860 --> 00:32:34,760
She was introduced by him in a sentence that left no gap.

743
00:32:35,320 --> 00:32:37,140
Rowina Pike, she's with me.

744
00:32:37,400 --> 00:32:38,340
It wasn't a description.

745
00:32:38,920 --> 00:32:39,700
It was a signature.

746
00:32:40,240 --> 00:32:42,760
The dinner advanced through courses she barely tasted.

747
00:32:43,340 --> 00:32:45,100
There was talk of an acquisition up north,

748
00:32:45,100 --> 00:32:47,300
of a land auction near the river,

749
00:32:47,660 --> 00:32:49,320
of a niece's wedding in Charleston.

750
00:32:50,040 --> 00:32:52,120
Rowina answered when addressed and listened,

751
00:32:52,420 --> 00:32:53,180
when not addressed.

752
00:32:53,680 --> 00:32:56,040
The wine was too good to be wasted on anxiety,

753
00:32:56,600 --> 00:32:58,980
so she drank slowly and kept her spine straight.

754
00:32:59,520 --> 00:33:02,300
At some point between the second course and the third,

755
00:33:02,600 --> 00:33:05,580
Jego's hand found hers on top of the white table cloth.

756
00:33:05,900 --> 00:33:08,300
He didn't hold it halfway or hide it under the table.

757
00:33:08,740 --> 00:33:10,980
He left his hand resting on top of her hand,

758
00:33:11,320 --> 00:33:12,560
in full view of everyone,

759
00:33:12,560 --> 00:33:15,180
and went on talking to the partner to his left,

760
00:33:15,600 --> 00:33:18,240
as if the hand was some object he'd found along the way,

761
00:33:18,520 --> 00:33:19,660
and decided to keep.

762
00:33:20,040 --> 00:33:21,360
Silas noticed first.

763
00:33:21,920 --> 00:33:24,100
Rowina saw the small flicker in the lawyer's eyes,

764
00:33:24,500 --> 00:33:25,300
almost invisible,

765
00:33:25,900 --> 00:33:28,460
followed by a throat clearing that made way for nothing.

766
00:33:28,980 --> 00:33:30,260
Jodora noticed next.

767
00:33:30,780 --> 00:33:32,820
The matriarch didn't take her eyes off her plate,

768
00:33:33,200 --> 00:33:35,540
but her fork paused half a second in the air,

769
00:33:35,940 --> 00:33:39,740
and resumed moving with a care Rowina had learned to interpret as reading.

770
00:33:40,340 --> 00:33:41,520
Jodora read people.

771
00:33:41,520 --> 00:33:43,280
She did it all the time,

772
00:33:43,600 --> 00:33:45,160
without appearing to be doing it.

773
00:33:45,500 --> 00:33:47,580
After coffee the partner's rose for cigars,

774
00:33:48,040 --> 00:33:50,060
and the wives went off to another parlor.

775
00:33:50,760 --> 00:33:51,840
Rowina went up alone.

776
00:33:52,220 --> 00:33:54,400
In the corridor she crossed paths with Silas,

777
00:33:54,920 --> 00:33:57,540
who carried a folder under his arm and a look she couldn't decipher,

778
00:33:58,200 --> 00:34:00,640
the kind of look that holds more than one interpretation,

779
00:34:01,240 --> 00:34:02,640
and gives away none.

780
00:34:03,220 --> 00:34:03,880
Good night, Miss.

781
00:34:04,200 --> 00:34:04,680
He said,

782
00:34:05,060 --> 00:34:06,780
Good night, Mr. Ashford.

783
00:34:07,200 --> 00:34:08,900
He seemed to want to say something more.

784
00:34:09,280 --> 00:34:11,280
He weighed the moment, decided against it,

785
00:34:11,280 --> 00:34:15,580
and went on down the corridor with the firm stride of someone with a set destination.

786
00:34:16,220 --> 00:34:19,940
In the guest room, Rowina shut the door and leaned against it for a moment.

787
00:34:20,420 --> 00:34:23,280
The wood was cold against her back through the fabric of the dress.

788
00:34:23,720 --> 00:34:25,400
She thought about tearing up the notes,

789
00:34:25,780 --> 00:34:29,260
she thought about calling Hollis and telling him the story didn't exist.

790
00:34:29,600 --> 00:34:31,840
She thought about telling Jago everything that night,

791
00:34:32,060 --> 00:34:34,720
with the wine still in her body and the courage of exhaustion.

792
00:34:35,200 --> 00:34:37,200
She thought about doing none of the three things,

793
00:34:37,720 --> 00:34:39,420
and leaving it all for the train back.

794
00:34:39,420 --> 00:34:43,580
She went to the bathroom, took off her makeup with cold water and cotton,

795
00:34:44,020 --> 00:34:47,220
put on a simple linen nightgown lay down on top of the bedspread,

796
00:34:47,760 --> 00:34:51,160
and stared at the white-washed ceiling as the house grew quiet,

797
00:34:51,840 --> 00:34:53,240
room by room.

798
00:34:53,540 --> 00:34:55,820
She fell asleep without realizing it.

799
00:34:55,980 --> 00:34:57,680
She was woken by the sound of the door.

800
00:34:58,120 --> 00:34:58,940
There was no knock.

801
00:34:59,360 --> 00:35:02,700
The door opened slowly, letting in a thin band of light from the corridor,

802
00:35:03,200 --> 00:35:06,720
and Rowina saw against that light, the silhouette of Jago quint.

803
00:35:07,260 --> 00:35:08,760
He didn't turn on the room's lamp.

804
00:35:08,760 --> 00:35:11,180
He walked to the middle of the room and stopped,

805
00:35:11,720 --> 00:35:13,920
and only then did she notice what was in his hands,

806
00:35:14,440 --> 00:35:18,740
the file, brown, no label, no rubber band now.

807
00:35:19,180 --> 00:35:21,440
Rowina sat up in the bed in a single motion.

808
00:35:21,940 --> 00:35:25,300
The air left her chest in an exhalation that made no sound.

809
00:35:25,720 --> 00:35:25,880
Help.

810
00:35:26,400 --> 00:35:28,400
Silas, he said, without raising his voice,

811
00:35:28,820 --> 00:35:30,840
he saw Odette prowling this corridor earlier.

812
00:35:31,300 --> 00:35:33,340
He thought it best I checked before she did.

813
00:35:33,760 --> 00:35:34,820
His voice was low.

814
00:35:35,220 --> 00:35:36,000
It was calm.

815
00:35:36,000 --> 00:35:39,080
It was empty of anything she could use to hold on to.

816
00:35:39,460 --> 00:35:41,440
Jago looked at the file he was carrying,

817
00:35:42,020 --> 00:35:45,020
leafed through a page she recognized without needing to look closely,

818
00:35:45,560 --> 00:35:47,260
and put the page back in its place,

819
00:35:47,580 --> 00:35:49,360
with a care that seemed in that moment,

820
00:35:49,820 --> 00:35:51,680
the cruelest thing in the world.

821
00:35:52,100 --> 00:35:53,540
Ballons sheets, he said,

822
00:35:53,980 --> 00:35:57,880
copies of old contracts, a list of names with notes beside them.

823
00:35:58,140 --> 00:35:59,960
I recognized at least three of the names.

824
00:36:00,320 --> 00:36:01,720
He lifted his eyes to her.

825
00:36:01,900 --> 00:36:02,960
This isn't an interview.

826
00:36:02,960 --> 00:36:05,120
It isn't, Rowina answered,

827
00:36:05,640 --> 00:36:07,800
because denying it would have been a worse insult.

828
00:36:08,340 --> 00:36:09,140
He nodded slightly.

829
00:36:09,780 --> 00:36:10,460
That was all.

830
00:36:10,860 --> 00:36:13,560
A single precise nod that didn't judge,

831
00:36:14,060 --> 00:36:15,940
and therefore weighed more than any judgment.

832
00:36:16,540 --> 00:36:17,800
You came here for this.

833
00:36:18,080 --> 00:36:19,880
I came here for this, she said,

834
00:36:20,280 --> 00:36:22,640
and I didn't know I would stop coming here for it.

835
00:36:22,780 --> 00:36:24,660
But I did stop weeks ago.

836
00:36:25,040 --> 00:36:27,280
I haven't opened that file once since.

837
00:36:27,560 --> 00:36:29,320
Here it doesn't matter, he cut in,

838
00:36:29,680 --> 00:36:32,140
and even cutting in he kept his usual low tone.

839
00:36:32,140 --> 00:36:34,840
You opened it yesterday, I heard you open it.

840
00:36:35,020 --> 00:36:36,380
I thought you were closing a suitcase.

841
00:36:37,200 --> 00:36:38,760
The silence settled between them,

842
00:36:38,920 --> 00:36:41,220
with a specificity, Rowina couldn't fill,

843
00:36:41,400 --> 00:36:42,740
and he didn't try to.

844
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:45,180
Jego, thank you for coming to Savannah,

845
00:36:45,520 --> 00:36:48,560
he said, and that was the sentence that went through her from side to side.

846
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:50,080
Thank you for the weeks.

847
00:36:50,580 --> 00:36:53,240
The interview is paid for, if you still want it.

848
00:36:53,460 --> 00:36:57,120
I only asked that you leave tomorrow morning before my mother comes down for coffee.

849
00:36:57,580 --> 00:37:00,140
She opened her mouth, closed it, opened it again.

850
00:37:00,140 --> 00:37:03,020
Don't do this like this, like what?

851
00:37:03,520 --> 00:37:06,100
Without yelling at me, he considered the sentence,

852
00:37:06,560 --> 00:37:10,480
he took too long to answer the kind of delay that is an answer in itself.

853
00:37:10,880 --> 00:37:12,960
If I yell you'll be able to think I'm still angry.

854
00:37:13,500 --> 00:37:15,980
His voice found a note she had never heard in him,

855
00:37:16,140 --> 00:37:17,420
too low to have a name.

856
00:37:17,960 --> 00:37:19,240
I don't want you to think that.

857
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:22,000
I want you to leave knowing exactly what stayed behind.

858
00:37:22,540 --> 00:37:23,660
It was worse than yelling.

859
00:37:24,180 --> 00:37:28,360
It was worse than anything she could have predicted that week or in any week before it.

860
00:37:28,360 --> 00:37:30,960
Jego set the file on the dresser near the door,

861
00:37:31,260 --> 00:37:34,120
with a precision that seemed calculated to make no noise.

862
00:37:34,620 --> 00:37:36,120
He didn't return it to her hand.

863
00:37:36,500 --> 00:37:37,900
He didn't take it with him.

864
00:37:38,040 --> 00:37:40,340
He left it there, in the middle of the way,

865
00:37:40,680 --> 00:37:44,480
like an exposed piece of evidence, neither of them needed to examine any more.

866
00:37:44,780 --> 00:37:46,140
Then he turned toward the door.

867
00:37:46,540 --> 00:37:47,060
Leave tomorrow.

868
00:37:47,600 --> 00:37:52,440
The door closed behind him with the most polite noise a door has ever produced in the entire world.

869
00:37:52,820 --> 00:37:54,400
Rhoina remained sitting on the bed.

870
00:37:54,400 --> 00:37:56,600
Her hands opened on the bed spread.

871
00:37:56,940 --> 00:37:59,920
Her heart beating in a rhythm she didn't recognize as her own.

872
00:38:00,380 --> 00:38:03,820
Outside in the corridor, his footsteps moved away slowly.

873
00:38:04,360 --> 00:38:05,980
No hurry, no hesitation.

874
00:38:06,700 --> 00:38:09,080
And at some point between her room and his room,

875
00:38:09,500 --> 00:38:11,620
they stopped for a second, before continuing.

876
00:38:12,260 --> 00:38:13,020
She didn't cry.

877
00:38:13,540 --> 00:38:14,020
Not yet.

878
00:38:14,300 --> 00:38:16,660
She kept looking at the file on top of the dresser,

879
00:38:16,940 --> 00:38:20,720
like someone staring at an animal that had followed her from too far away,

880
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:22,520
to now pretend it was a stranger.

881
00:38:22,520 --> 00:38:26,080
Outside the window, the garden of the Quint Mansion,

882
00:38:26,840 --> 00:38:32,060
breathed the humid night, the smell of earth and jasmine rising with the breeze off the river.

883
00:38:32,460 --> 00:38:35,500
Somewhere near the water, a real owl called out once.

884
00:38:36,080 --> 00:38:38,520
Rhoina thought of the glass owl set with red stone,

885
00:38:38,960 --> 00:38:41,540
tucked in a dark velvet box at the bottom of her bag,

886
00:38:41,980 --> 00:38:45,920
and felt that this was the memory that would hurt most on the train the next day.

887
00:38:46,480 --> 00:38:49,400
But chapter 5 killing the story.

888
00:38:50,660 --> 00:38:54,280
Rain back left before 8, and Rhoina sat by the window,

889
00:38:54,680 --> 00:38:57,140
because the aisle required looking at people head on,

890
00:38:57,480 --> 00:39:01,400
and people that morning would have seen what she hadn't yet seen in the mirror.

891
00:39:01,900 --> 00:39:04,200
She rested her forehead against the cold glass,

892
00:39:04,660 --> 00:39:07,360
and stayed that way for a length of time she couldn't measure.

893
00:39:07,940 --> 00:39:12,920
Savannah fell behind in pieces, a roof, a tower, a line of trees bent by the river wind,

894
00:39:13,420 --> 00:39:15,400
and none of it hurt with the noise she had expected.

895
00:39:15,400 --> 00:39:19,100
It hurt low. It hurt the way Jago had said,

896
00:39:19,280 --> 00:39:22,500
thank you in the small hours, when she was expecting a shout,

897
00:39:22,880 --> 00:39:25,300
anything with enough volume for her to push back against,

898
00:39:25,820 --> 00:39:28,240
the file was still on top of the guest room dresser.

899
00:39:28,520 --> 00:39:32,120
She hadn't even asked for it back, leaving it there felt fair.

900
00:39:32,360 --> 00:39:35,820
In the sense that justice is what's left over when everything else surrenders.

901
00:39:36,280 --> 00:39:39,680
She didn't cry on the train. She counted roof panels of cars,

902
00:39:40,300 --> 00:39:45,000
counted poles, counted the times the conductor passed down the aisle dragging a coffee cart.

903
00:39:45,400 --> 00:39:48,360
The smell of the machine coffee was cheap, and watery.

904
00:39:48,940 --> 00:39:53,300
Nothing like what Jago had learned to make, and that idiotic detail was what came

905
00:39:53,300 --> 00:39:57,160
closest to breaking her. She reached the grey city just before noon.

906
00:39:57,520 --> 00:40:00,100
The station smelled of lubricant and cheap bread.

907
00:40:00,600 --> 00:40:03,160
Rowena carried her suitcase like someone carrying a witness.

908
00:40:03,640 --> 00:40:05,280
She cried in the newsroom bathroom.

909
00:40:05,620 --> 00:40:07,380
It was a dry cry of two minutes.

910
00:40:07,880 --> 00:40:12,580
Curled up in a stall with her hand over her mouth because Marlo Trent was on the other side of the door.

911
00:40:12,580 --> 00:40:16,320
Tapping the tip of her shoe and speaking loudly to cover for her.

912
00:40:16,560 --> 00:40:19,560
Come out of their pike. If you stay in there any longer,

913
00:40:19,920 --> 00:40:22,900
Hollis is going to knock on the door and then I'm going to have to bite him.

914
00:40:23,180 --> 00:40:25,980
Rowena laughed in the middle of the cry without meaning to.

915
00:40:26,260 --> 00:40:28,180
It was an ugly sound but it worked.

916
00:40:28,640 --> 00:40:32,540
She came out with her face washed. Marlo looked at her for a whole second,

917
00:40:33,040 --> 00:40:35,280
without sarcasm for the first time in years.

918
00:40:35,780 --> 00:40:37,760
There was something different in her friend's expression.

919
00:40:38,340 --> 00:40:39,320
The shoulders quieter.

920
00:40:39,320 --> 00:40:42,320
The way she stood still without her phone in her hand.

921
00:40:42,800 --> 00:40:45,440
You okay? No. Rowena answered.

922
00:40:46,000 --> 00:40:51,380
But I will be. Marlo squeezed her shoulder and her hand stayed there too long for a joke.

923
00:40:51,780 --> 00:40:55,340
That was how Rowena understood her friend had guessed everything before asking.

924
00:40:55,940 --> 00:40:57,700
The newsroom had that midday noise.

925
00:40:58,200 --> 00:41:00,360
Keys, phones ringing two desks over.

926
00:41:00,680 --> 00:41:04,920
Someone shouting a page number down the hall as if the whole building needed to know.

927
00:41:04,920 --> 00:41:10,040
Hollis Vaughan lifted his eyes over his glasses the moment Rowena passed down the central aisle.

928
00:41:10,500 --> 00:41:13,300
He didn't smile. He didn't ask how the trip had gone.

929
00:41:13,700 --> 00:41:16,420
He simply pointed with his pen to the door of his office.

930
00:41:16,780 --> 00:41:18,580
A short, habitual gesture.

931
00:41:19,060 --> 00:41:20,860
The kind that allows no negotiation.

932
00:41:21,540 --> 00:41:23,980
She went in. She shut the door behind her.

933
00:41:24,240 --> 00:41:28,240
That office smelled of aged paper and coffee no one had the courage to throw out.

934
00:41:28,600 --> 00:41:32,560
And there was a plant in the corner that had been dying for at least two months.

935
00:41:32,560 --> 00:41:37,140
It's leaves drooping over the edge of the pot without anyone having noticed.

936
00:41:37,660 --> 00:41:38,920
Hollis sat down his pen.

937
00:41:39,360 --> 00:41:40,280
Headline, he said.

938
00:41:40,760 --> 00:41:41,400
End of the day.

939
00:41:41,900 --> 00:41:43,200
There's not going to be a headline.

940
00:41:43,800 --> 00:41:44,860
Hollis blinked once.

941
00:41:45,380 --> 00:41:46,480
He leaned back in his chair.

942
00:41:46,980 --> 00:41:47,860
Say that again.

943
00:41:48,240 --> 00:41:52,280
There's not going to be a headline Rowena repeated and her voice came out firm

944
00:41:52,280 --> 00:41:53,160
of them she expected.

945
00:41:53,680 --> 00:41:55,860
I'm not going to deliver what you asked for.

946
00:41:56,040 --> 00:41:58,480
Not today, not next week, not ever.

947
00:41:58,960 --> 00:42:00,720
You went there with a mission pike.

948
00:42:00,720 --> 00:42:03,900
I did, and I came back without it.

949
00:42:04,160 --> 00:42:05,760
Hollis looked at the desk for a moment.

950
00:42:06,240 --> 00:42:09,460
When he raised his eyes, there was less anger than she'd imagined.

951
00:42:10,060 --> 00:42:14,480
And more a kind of old disappointment, the kind of disappointment bosses carry from other

952
00:42:14,480 --> 00:42:19,020
bosses before them, piled up over years in rooms exactly like that one.

953
00:42:19,200 --> 00:42:20,280
You know what this means.

954
00:42:20,860 --> 00:42:21,280
I do.

955
00:42:21,840 --> 00:42:23,880
Rowena set a folded paper on the desk.

956
00:42:24,240 --> 00:42:26,620
I'm handing this over before you have to say it.

957
00:42:27,040 --> 00:42:28,120
Hollis picked up the paper.

958
00:42:28,440 --> 00:42:29,660
He didn't open it.

959
00:42:29,660 --> 00:42:30,160
Why?

960
00:42:30,520 --> 00:42:30,960
He asked.

961
00:42:31,320 --> 00:42:35,960
And the question came almost gentle, which frightened her more than an insult would have.

962
00:42:36,300 --> 00:42:37,680
Rowena was silent for a second.

963
00:42:38,060 --> 00:42:40,060
She thought of a pretty professional answer.

964
00:42:40,560 --> 00:42:42,140
The kind that looks good in retrospect.

965
00:42:42,580 --> 00:42:43,340
She gave up.

966
00:42:43,620 --> 00:42:46,240
Because the story stopped existing, she said.

967
00:42:46,600 --> 00:42:47,780
He stopped being a story.

968
00:42:48,280 --> 00:42:51,100
And I don't know how to write about someone who became a person.

969
00:42:51,440 --> 00:42:55,940
Hollis looked at her for a long time, with the expression of someone re-reading an equation that

970
00:42:55,940 --> 00:42:59,580
doesn't add up, then he nodded once, almost imperceptibly.

971
00:43:00,080 --> 00:43:02,420
Get out before I change my mind, he said.

972
00:43:02,840 --> 00:43:04,880
And Pike, she stopped at the door.

973
00:43:05,340 --> 00:43:06,000
You were good.

974
00:43:06,400 --> 00:43:07,880
Rowena swallowed before answering.

975
00:43:08,480 --> 00:43:09,160
I still am.

976
00:43:09,600 --> 00:43:10,540
Just not for this.

977
00:43:10,960 --> 00:43:12,080
She shut the door carefully.

978
00:43:12,720 --> 00:43:17,080
Hollis was leaning against the corridor wall, waiting with two cups of machine coffee.

979
00:43:17,560 --> 00:43:22,420
And she pushed one of the cups into Rowena's hand without ceremony, like someone handing over a

980
00:43:22,420 --> 00:43:23,260
survival item.

981
00:43:23,640 --> 00:43:24,520
Did you do it?

982
00:43:24,720 --> 00:43:25,220
She asked.

983
00:43:25,220 --> 00:43:26,120
I did.

984
00:43:26,740 --> 00:43:27,020
Shit.

985
00:43:27,680 --> 00:43:28,780
Marlo Blue on the coffee.

986
00:43:29,460 --> 00:43:31,640
Welcome to the club of the dignified unemployed.

987
00:43:32,580 --> 00:43:33,180
Rowena laughed.

988
00:43:33,660 --> 00:43:36,780
It was a short, broken laugh, but it was a laugh.

989
00:43:37,220 --> 00:43:39,120
They went down the stairs instead of the elevator.

990
00:43:39,780 --> 00:43:43,280
On the sidewalk, the city was grey the way it had always been.

991
00:43:43,700 --> 00:43:48,060
And Rowena looked at the buildings without any of the glow that Savannah painted on to even a

992
00:43:48,060 --> 00:43:48,880
cloudy morning.

993
00:43:49,360 --> 00:43:51,420
Something was missing from that sky.

994
00:43:51,860 --> 00:43:53,780
The smell of Magnolia was missing.

995
00:43:53,780 --> 00:43:58,220
The way the Savannah river appeared between two streets when no one expected it.

996
00:43:58,420 --> 00:44:02,860
A strip of lead-coloured water that somehow made everything lighter was missing.

997
00:44:03,320 --> 00:44:04,440
E was missing.

998
00:44:04,940 --> 00:44:07,660
You're going back, Marlo said, without asking.

999
00:44:08,260 --> 00:44:08,860
I am.

1000
00:44:09,240 --> 00:44:10,140
Will he take you back?

1001
00:44:10,560 --> 00:44:11,200
I don't know.

1002
00:44:11,520 --> 00:44:11,940
He will.

1003
00:44:12,340 --> 00:44:14,320
Marlo insisted looking off into the distance.

1004
00:44:14,960 --> 00:44:19,360
A man who sends for you three weeks in a row doesn't close a door for good.

1005
00:44:19,760 --> 00:44:20,580
He locks it.

1006
00:44:20,840 --> 00:44:21,460
It's different.

1007
00:44:21,460 --> 00:44:24,320
Rowena looked at her friend, and for an instant,

1008
00:44:24,840 --> 00:44:26,540
the world stopped spinning so fast.

1009
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:27,400
Marlo.

1010
00:44:27,960 --> 00:44:28,180
What?

1011
00:44:28,660 --> 00:44:29,280
Thank you.

1012
00:44:29,540 --> 00:44:31,640
Get out of here before I cry, Pike.

1013
00:44:32,120 --> 00:44:33,320
It doesn't suit me.

1014
00:44:33,800 --> 00:44:37,660
Rowena took the night train and slept enough not to look devastated on arrival.

1015
00:44:38,080 --> 00:44:42,600
The car smelled of old fabric and rain, and she kept her face turned to the dark window

1016
00:44:42,600 --> 00:44:46,820
for much of the trip, watching her own reflection without being able to look away.

1017
00:44:47,320 --> 00:44:51,440
On Sunday morning, Savannah received the train with the sun coming in from the side.

1018
00:44:51,440 --> 00:44:54,680
And the whole station smelled of bakery and river breeze,

1019
00:44:55,240 --> 00:44:57,180
she took a taxi without stopping to think.

1020
00:44:57,580 --> 00:44:58,880
She went in through the front.

1021
00:44:59,360 --> 00:45:00,140
She rang the bell.

1022
00:45:00,800 --> 00:45:01,220
Feeling answered.

1023
00:45:01,700 --> 00:45:05,520
His eyes widened for half a second, before returning to normal trained.

1024
00:45:06,100 --> 00:45:08,100
Miss Pike, I need to talk to him.

1025
00:45:08,300 --> 00:45:09,700
He's in his office with guests.

1026
00:45:10,260 --> 00:45:10,860
I know.

1027
00:45:11,320 --> 00:45:12,180
Feeling hesitated.

1028
00:45:12,780 --> 00:45:13,760
Then he stepped aside.

1029
00:45:14,300 --> 00:45:15,920
Miss is quint arrived in our ego.

1030
00:45:16,160 --> 00:45:18,160
He said quietly, almost a warning.

1031
00:45:18,740 --> 00:45:20,400
And Miss Martian came along.

1032
00:45:20,400 --> 00:45:21,760
Rowena nodded.

1033
00:45:22,060 --> 00:45:24,780
Druid deep breath once and walked down the marble corridor.

1034
00:45:25,360 --> 00:45:27,940
Like someone walking to a trial she herself had scheduled.

1035
00:45:28,540 --> 00:45:30,840
The corridor was silent except for her own footsteps.

1036
00:45:31,480 --> 00:45:35,420
And their echo on the old tiles sounded too firm for the way she was feeling inside.

1037
00:45:36,000 --> 00:45:39,840
Jay goes office was in the west wing of the mansion, and the door was a jar.

1038
00:45:40,280 --> 00:45:45,180
She heard before she saw, the voice of Odette Martian, sweet, too loud,

1039
00:45:45,660 --> 00:45:49,780
that voice of someone who pretends to console and measures the effect in a mirror.

1040
00:45:49,780 --> 00:45:52,180
A necessary evil you'dora.

1041
00:45:52,640 --> 00:45:57,780
Truly, better to find out now than, Rowena opened the door before Odette finished.

1042
00:45:58,300 --> 00:45:59,640
The entire office went still.

1043
00:46:00,180 --> 00:46:03,900
Jay goes to behind the desk, dark jacket hands resting on the top.

1044
00:46:04,260 --> 00:46:06,920
You'dora seated in the green velvet armchair near the window,

1045
00:46:07,440 --> 00:46:11,120
back straight as ever, as if her posture were the last line of defense.

1046
00:46:11,800 --> 00:46:13,600
Silas leaning against the bookcase.

1047
00:46:14,040 --> 00:46:14,900
Neutral expression.

1048
00:46:15,500 --> 00:46:18,360
Eyes that recognized Rowena before the rest of his body did.

1049
00:46:18,360 --> 00:46:24,360
Odette on the sofa, glass in hand, a smile dressing her mouth until it froze when she saw

1050
00:46:24,360 --> 00:46:25,340
who had come in.

1051
00:46:25,680 --> 00:46:26,680
Jaygo didn't move.

1052
00:46:27,060 --> 00:46:28,620
Only his jaw tensed once.

1053
00:46:29,200 --> 00:46:33,440
Rowena said Silas almost automatically, trying to smooth things over.

1054
00:46:33,820 --> 00:46:36,880
Stay, Rowena asked, without taking her eyes off Jaygo.

1055
00:46:37,440 --> 00:46:38,100
All of you.

1056
00:46:38,400 --> 00:46:38,660
Stay.

1057
00:46:39,240 --> 00:46:40,340
Odette opened her mouth.

1058
00:46:40,840 --> 00:46:42,220
Rowena gave her no chance.

1059
00:46:42,720 --> 00:46:44,880
I came to tell the truth, she said.

1060
00:46:45,240 --> 00:46:45,900
All of it.

1061
00:46:45,900 --> 00:46:50,540
I'm not going to apologise first because an apology before the truth is an insult.

1062
00:46:51,180 --> 00:46:52,440
Odora raised an eyebrow.

1063
00:46:52,800 --> 00:46:53,580
Nothing more.

1064
00:46:53,960 --> 00:46:54,800
Rowena breathed.

1065
00:46:55,260 --> 00:46:59,440
Her voice came out firm, even though her hands trembled inside her jacket.

1066
00:46:59,960 --> 00:47:01,740
I came to Savannah with two missions.

1067
00:47:02,380 --> 00:47:03,400
The interview was one.

1068
00:47:03,780 --> 00:47:07,160
The other was to come back with material that would destroy the Quint family.

1069
00:47:07,680 --> 00:47:11,740
My editor wanted a scandal story, and I accepted because I needed the job.

1070
00:47:12,200 --> 00:47:15,240
I accepted believing I could separate the work from the charade.

1071
00:47:15,240 --> 00:47:16,300
She paused.

1072
00:47:16,860 --> 00:47:17,580
I couldn't.

1073
00:47:17,860 --> 00:47:20,160
Odette let out a low incredulous laugh.

1074
00:47:20,500 --> 00:47:21,700
No one joined her.

1075
00:47:21,880 --> 00:47:25,520
I brought the file, Rowena continued, and her voice didn't waver.

1076
00:47:26,040 --> 00:47:27,560
You already know I brought it.

1077
00:47:27,760 --> 00:47:28,500
It was found.

1078
00:47:28,980 --> 00:47:29,580
It was red.

1079
00:47:30,140 --> 00:47:33,600
And it was returned in the small hours of yesterday morning with a thank you

1080
00:47:33,600 --> 00:47:35,820
that hurt more than any shout would have.

1081
00:47:36,080 --> 00:47:36,940
She looked at Jaygo.

1082
00:47:37,420 --> 00:47:38,140
He didn't look away.

1083
00:47:38,600 --> 00:47:39,380
He didn't confirm.

1084
00:47:39,960 --> 00:47:44,620
His face was that of a man counting every word before deciding what to do with them.

1085
00:47:44,620 --> 00:47:50,040
I could have gone back to the newsroom, written what my editor wanted, saved my career.

1086
00:47:50,540 --> 00:47:52,100
A voice rose half a tone.

1087
00:47:52,480 --> 00:47:53,540
I didn't write it.

1088
00:47:53,680 --> 00:47:55,140
I killed the story this morning.

1089
00:47:55,560 --> 00:47:57,460
I resigned before he could fire me.

1090
00:47:57,760 --> 00:47:58,860
There's no story anymore.

1091
00:47:59,340 --> 00:48:00,500
There's no file anymore.

1092
00:48:01,000 --> 00:48:03,820
There's nothing left in that guest room that's of use to anyone.

1093
00:48:04,220 --> 00:48:06,040
She took a step forward just one.

1094
00:48:06,340 --> 00:48:07,920
And I didn't come here for forgiveness.

1095
00:48:08,520 --> 00:48:12,240
I came because if I didn't say this in front of everyone who watched the lie happen,

1096
00:48:12,240 --> 00:48:16,040
the truth would remain a private thing and the lie was public.

1097
00:48:16,500 --> 00:48:17,480
That's not fair.

1098
00:48:18,020 --> 00:48:18,840
Total silence.

1099
00:48:19,520 --> 00:48:20,640
Udora blinked once.

1100
00:48:21,100 --> 00:48:21,380
Slowly.

1101
00:48:21,980 --> 00:48:24,880
Like someone recalculating something she'd thought was settled.

1102
00:48:25,400 --> 00:48:27,980
O'Dette looked at her glasses if it had betrayed her.

1103
00:48:28,140 --> 00:48:29,180
I dropped the story.

1104
00:48:29,580 --> 00:48:30,220
Rowena said.

1105
00:48:30,560 --> 00:48:31,800
And her voice lowered again.

1106
00:48:32,300 --> 00:48:33,100
Almost soft.

1107
00:48:33,540 --> 00:48:35,340
Because he stopped being a story.

1108
00:48:35,840 --> 00:48:38,480
I couldn't write about a man who learned my coffee by heart.

1109
00:48:38,860 --> 00:48:39,440
She finished.

1110
00:48:39,440 --> 00:48:41,100
The hands were still trembling.

1111
00:48:41,640 --> 00:48:42,660
She let them tremble.

1112
00:48:43,160 --> 00:48:44,100
O'Dette rose first.

1113
00:48:44,300 --> 00:48:46,560
Her glass coming down hard on the side tray.

1114
00:48:46,960 --> 00:48:47,800
What a spectacle.

1115
00:48:48,340 --> 00:48:48,940
She said.

1116
00:48:49,340 --> 00:48:50,400
Seeking Jago's eyes.

1117
00:48:50,920 --> 00:48:52,500
You're not going to believe this are you?

1118
00:48:52,980 --> 00:48:54,340
Jago didn't answer O'Dette.

1119
00:48:54,860 --> 00:48:57,980
He looked at Rowena for a length of time no one there could count.

1120
00:48:58,400 --> 00:49:01,400
Then he pulled back his chair unhurried and stood up.

1121
00:49:02,740 --> 00:49:02,760
J.

1122
00:49:02,880 --> 00:49:04,320
Chapter 6 His laugh.

1123
00:49:06,290 --> 00:49:08,370
Go cross the office in a single stride.

1124
00:49:08,370 --> 00:49:11,530
It didn't seem like a stride it seemed like decision walking.

1125
00:49:12,130 --> 00:49:15,670
Rowena didn't step back but she held her breath in the middle of her chest

1126
00:49:15,670 --> 00:49:18,170
as if her body had forgotten how to do it.

1127
00:49:18,330 --> 00:49:20,050
He stopped half a meter from her.

1128
00:49:20,250 --> 00:49:21,250
He didn't touch her.

1129
00:49:21,570 --> 00:49:22,830
He just stood there.

1130
00:49:23,070 --> 00:49:24,470
His eyes fixed on her.

1131
00:49:24,790 --> 00:49:27,430
And there was something in that gaze Rowena couldn't name.

1132
00:49:27,850 --> 00:49:29,230
Neither anger nor relief.

1133
00:49:29,750 --> 00:49:31,590
Something that made her hold her own breath.

1134
00:49:32,010 --> 00:49:32,450
O'Dette.

1135
00:49:32,730 --> 00:49:34,170
He said without looking back.

1136
00:49:34,410 --> 00:49:35,370
Get out of my house.

1137
00:49:35,870 --> 00:49:37,450
The silence in the room had weight.

1138
00:49:37,450 --> 00:49:40,930
The kind of silence that makes people hold their breath without realizing.

1139
00:49:41,690 --> 00:49:41,970
Jago.

1140
00:49:42,630 --> 00:49:44,690
Now, his voice came out low.

1141
00:49:45,190 --> 00:49:45,310
Curtis.

1142
00:49:45,970 --> 00:49:47,190
The way he spoke to everyone.

1143
00:49:47,810 --> 00:49:50,370
And even so, no one in the room had any doubt.

1144
00:49:50,850 --> 00:49:54,270
O'Dette picked up her bag with rigid movements her fingers gripping the leather.

1145
00:49:54,670 --> 00:49:55,810
She didn't look at you, Dora.

1146
00:49:56,290 --> 00:49:59,630
The door slammed behind her with the thin noise of high heels

1147
00:49:59,630 --> 00:50:01,130
that had lost their audience.

1148
00:50:01,750 --> 00:50:03,030
Jago breathed once.

1149
00:50:03,350 --> 00:50:07,270
Then he looked at Rowena as if he were checking a calculation that had taken

1150
00:50:07,270 --> 00:50:08,870
far too long to add up.

1151
00:50:09,130 --> 00:50:11,150
I want you to hear this," he said.

1152
00:50:11,430 --> 00:50:14,410
Loud enough for siless and you Dora to hear every word.

1153
00:50:14,850 --> 00:50:17,950
And loud enough to carry through the open door and reach the corridor.

1154
00:50:18,510 --> 00:50:21,490
Where half a dozen of you Dora's guests pretended not to listen.

1155
00:50:21,970 --> 00:50:22,630
She stays.

1156
00:50:23,230 --> 00:50:23,830
With me.

1157
00:50:24,170 --> 00:50:29,330
And tomorrow, all of Savannah will hear it from my mouth before hearing it from anyone else's.

1158
00:50:29,490 --> 00:50:32,550
He paused for an instant, as if the sentence carried weight.

1159
00:50:33,010 --> 00:50:34,650
I'm done letting fear choose for me.

1160
00:50:35,050 --> 00:50:36,390
He raised his hand slowly.

1161
00:50:36,390 --> 00:50:38,910
He touched the tips of his fingers to her chin.

1162
00:50:39,310 --> 00:50:40,850
The touch has light as a question.

1163
00:50:41,570 --> 00:50:41,790
Stay.

1164
00:50:42,490 --> 00:50:43,910
Rowena felt her eyes sting.

1165
00:50:44,410 --> 00:50:45,250
She didn't look away.

1166
00:50:45,790 --> 00:50:46,330
I'll stay.

1167
00:50:46,850 --> 00:50:48,550
Silas let out the air he'd been holding.

1168
00:50:49,090 --> 00:50:50,190
Udora didn't move.

1169
00:50:50,570 --> 00:50:53,230
But something in the line of her shoulders gave way a millimeter.

1170
00:50:53,750 --> 00:50:56,370
It was the matriarch who broke the silence at last,

1171
00:50:56,790 --> 00:50:59,590
with that voice that never missed its tone even on hard days.

1172
00:51:00,090 --> 00:51:03,190
Out of here, she said, addressing neither of them in particular.

1173
00:51:03,770 --> 00:51:05,150
All of you I need to think.

1174
00:51:05,150 --> 00:51:07,410
Rowena and Jago left together.

1175
00:51:07,890 --> 00:51:10,410
Silas closed the door with the care of someone who knows

1176
00:51:10,410 --> 00:51:14,230
that a well-closed door is sometimes worth an entire contract.

1177
00:51:14,750 --> 00:51:16,970
In the corridor Jago held Rowena's hand.

1178
00:51:17,410 --> 00:51:18,150
That was all.

1179
00:51:18,530 --> 00:51:19,530
He didn't kiss her.

1180
00:51:19,710 --> 00:51:20,370
He didn't speak.

1181
00:51:20,870 --> 00:51:22,390
He just held it.

1182
00:51:22,550 --> 00:51:25,630
His fingers laced through hers with a quiet firmness.

1183
00:51:26,150 --> 00:51:28,330
Unlike anything she'd known in him until then.

1184
00:51:28,710 --> 00:51:30,370
He let her out onto the back porch.

1185
00:51:30,870 --> 00:51:32,490
The one facing the Savannah River.

1186
00:51:32,490 --> 00:51:35,770
The late afternoon sun fell gold and on the water,

1187
00:51:36,250 --> 00:51:38,190
tinting the surface copper and amber,

1188
00:51:38,570 --> 00:51:42,930
and the smell of the garden came heavy with magnolia wet from the night before.

1189
00:51:43,410 --> 00:51:47,630
Somewhere in the middle of the garden, an insect sang the same repeated note,

1190
00:51:47,970 --> 00:51:49,450
Rhythmic in No Harry.

1191
00:51:49,970 --> 00:51:53,270
You killed the story, said Jago, looking at the river.

1192
00:51:53,690 --> 00:51:54,710
It wasn't a question.

1193
00:51:55,310 --> 00:51:55,730
I did.

1194
00:51:56,210 --> 00:51:57,250
You lost your job.

1195
00:51:57,870 --> 00:51:58,130
I did.

1196
00:51:58,630 --> 00:51:59,710
He turned his head slowly,

1197
00:51:59,710 --> 00:52:03,130
and his profile against the late afternoon light had a hardness

1198
00:52:03,130 --> 00:52:04,730
Rowena couldn't read in full.

1199
00:52:05,250 --> 00:52:06,930
She could only read the part that mattered.

1200
00:52:07,410 --> 00:52:09,690
I'm going to help you find another one, he said.

1201
00:52:10,090 --> 00:52:10,830
One you choose.

1202
00:52:11,350 --> 00:52:12,770
Not one I choose for you.

1203
00:52:13,290 --> 00:52:14,250
Rowena laughed softly.

1204
00:52:14,810 --> 00:52:15,870
The laugh came out choked.

1205
00:52:16,350 --> 00:52:16,950
A little crooked.

1206
00:52:17,450 --> 00:52:20,190
The way laughs happen when the body doesn't quite know yet,

1207
00:52:20,430 --> 00:52:22,070
whether it's crying or smiling.

1208
00:52:22,650 --> 00:52:24,770
You said choose and for you.

1209
00:52:24,970 --> 00:52:26,190
In the same sentence, quint.

1210
00:52:26,750 --> 00:52:27,050
Careful.

1211
00:52:27,670 --> 00:52:29,090
He closed his eyes for a second.

1212
00:52:29,090 --> 00:52:32,470
When he opened them, his shoulders had dropped half a finger,

1213
00:52:32,970 --> 00:52:36,690
and his mouth gave way in a near smile Rowena had never seen there.

1214
00:52:36,970 --> 00:52:37,510
I'll learn.

1215
00:52:37,970 --> 00:52:41,390
It was there behind them that the porch door opened.

1216
00:52:41,950 --> 00:52:44,250
Yudora came out without announcing herself.

1217
00:52:44,530 --> 00:52:45,950
She didn't look at Jago first.

1218
00:52:46,310 --> 00:52:49,270
She looked at Rowena, and there was in that gaze and a

1219
00:52:49,270 --> 00:52:52,790
preysal different from the earlier ones without the usual scalpel.

1220
00:52:53,210 --> 00:52:55,290
The matriarch crossed the stone floor,

1221
00:52:55,750 --> 00:52:56,990
and stopped in front of her.

1222
00:52:56,990 --> 00:52:59,670
Up close in the low rosy light of that afternoon,

1223
00:53:00,370 --> 00:53:02,410
Yudora seemed smaller than on the night of the ball.

1224
00:53:03,010 --> 00:53:05,270
Smaller and older and less sharp,

1225
00:53:05,610 --> 00:53:07,910
as if she'd left her armor hanging on the inside.

1226
00:53:08,470 --> 00:53:10,730
Rowena waited for the blow that didn't come.

1227
00:53:11,170 --> 00:53:12,550
Yudora extended her hand.

1228
00:53:12,970 --> 00:53:14,630
She touched Rowena's arm lightly.

1229
00:53:15,190 --> 00:53:17,450
A thumb sliding once over the sleeve of the jacket.

1230
00:53:18,070 --> 00:53:21,210
A gesture so restrained it could have gone unnoticed, but it didn't.

1231
00:53:21,490 --> 00:53:23,990
Then she turned her head and looked into the hall.

1232
00:53:24,230 --> 00:53:25,450
The wide door was open.

1233
00:53:25,450 --> 00:53:27,770
And from there you could see the empty chair.

1234
00:53:28,130 --> 00:53:30,670
The one that had always been near the window of the main hall.

1235
00:53:30,990 --> 00:53:32,910
Its back turned slightly to the side,

1236
00:53:33,250 --> 00:53:36,130
as if someone had just stood up and would come back at any moment.

1237
00:53:36,650 --> 00:53:39,370
Yudora kept looking long enough for the moment to grow heavy.

1238
00:53:39,850 --> 00:53:41,570
You have his laugh, she murmured.

1239
00:53:42,110 --> 00:53:43,230
Rowena didn't understand.

1240
00:53:43,790 --> 00:53:45,570
She felt her heart skipped a whole beat,

1241
00:53:45,910 --> 00:53:47,050
but she didn't understand.

1242
00:53:47,710 --> 00:53:48,790
Yudora didn't explain.

1243
00:53:49,190 --> 00:53:51,350
She just squeezed her arm once very lightly,

1244
00:53:51,830 --> 00:53:52,850
and went back inside.

1245
00:53:52,850 --> 00:53:55,350
The door closed behind her without a sound.

1246
00:53:55,850 --> 00:53:58,390
As if the house were protecting that secret too.

1247
00:53:58,750 --> 00:53:59,910
Rowena looked at Jago.

1248
00:54:00,390 --> 00:54:01,430
His jaw was locked.

1249
00:54:01,730 --> 00:54:03,910
His gaze fixed on some point of the river

1250
00:54:03,910 --> 00:54:06,010
that no longer belonged to that afternoon.

1251
00:54:06,710 --> 00:54:07,130
Jago.

1252
00:54:07,730 --> 00:54:09,070
Later, he said quietly.

1253
00:54:09,690 --> 00:54:11,390
Please, she didn't insist.

1254
00:54:11,910 --> 00:54:15,150
She stored the question in the same place where she stored all the details

1255
00:54:15,150 --> 00:54:16,910
that didn't yet have a frame.

1256
00:54:17,250 --> 00:54:20,330
She kept storing, because that was what she knew how to do.

1257
00:54:20,330 --> 00:54:24,230
And because not every detail asked to be opened on the same day it appeared.

1258
00:54:24,730 --> 00:54:27,010
Yudora back inside at the end of the afternoon.

1259
00:54:27,590 --> 00:54:29,270
When the river was already dark blue,

1260
00:54:29,730 --> 00:54:32,530
and the mansions lights were beginning to come on one by one,

1261
00:54:32,850 --> 00:54:34,030
as if the house were breathing.

1262
00:54:34,590 --> 00:54:35,430
They ate little.

1263
00:54:35,770 --> 00:54:36,730
No one spoke much.

1264
00:54:37,310 --> 00:54:39,090
Silas passed down the corridor once,

1265
00:54:39,530 --> 00:54:42,290
nodded agreeding, and vanished off towards the library.

1266
00:54:42,790 --> 00:54:46,890
Nive brought T without asking, and disappeared before anyone could thank her.

1267
00:54:47,110 --> 00:54:49,170
Then it was Jago who extended his hand.

1268
00:54:49,170 --> 00:54:50,490
Rowen were accepted.

1269
00:54:50,950 --> 00:54:52,950
They went up the main staircase together.

1270
00:54:53,370 --> 00:54:55,170
Her footsteps echoed on the marble.

1271
00:54:55,670 --> 00:54:57,350
His almost didn't.

1272
00:54:57,670 --> 00:55:00,950
He always stepped as if he didn't want to take up more space than necessary.

1273
00:55:01,570 --> 00:55:02,850
Half way up the stairs he stopped.

1274
00:55:03,390 --> 00:55:04,270
He turned her slowly.

1275
00:55:04,830 --> 00:55:06,830
His hand displayed against the nape of her neck,

1276
00:55:07,190 --> 00:55:10,630
and pressed his forehead to hers for a length of time that belonged to no clock.

1277
00:55:10,930 --> 00:55:12,430
I don't know how to do this right.

1278
00:55:12,790 --> 00:55:15,110
He said, too low to be anything but honest.

1279
00:55:15,710 --> 00:55:16,430
No one does.

1280
00:55:16,930 --> 00:55:17,390
He laughed.

1281
00:55:17,390 --> 00:55:19,670
It was a short laugh almost startled.

1282
00:55:20,110 --> 00:55:23,370
The kind of laugh that escapes before a person decides to let it out.

1283
00:55:23,730 --> 00:55:25,170
Rowen restored that laugh too.

1284
00:55:25,350 --> 00:55:28,070
She stored it the same way she stored everything that mattered.

1285
00:55:28,470 --> 00:55:31,110
Without noting it down, without recording it.

1286
00:55:31,330 --> 00:55:33,190
Just letting it settle deep.

1287
00:55:33,610 --> 00:55:34,650
They kept going up.

1288
00:55:34,850 --> 00:55:37,850
At the top the corridor had that late night mansion silence,

1289
00:55:38,290 --> 00:55:39,790
that isn't the silence of emptiness.

1290
00:55:40,430 --> 00:55:41,750
It's the silence of care.

1291
00:55:42,210 --> 00:55:43,750
The door to his room was a jar.

1292
00:55:44,210 --> 00:55:45,850
He pushed it with the back of his hand.

1293
00:55:45,850 --> 00:55:48,790
A casual gesture that contained a whole decision.

1294
00:55:49,410 --> 00:55:50,010
She went in.

1295
00:55:50,310 --> 00:55:51,670
He went in behind her.

1296
00:55:51,930 --> 00:55:53,170
The door closed slowly.

1297
00:55:53,750 --> 00:55:54,150
The kitchen.

1298
00:55:54,710 --> 00:55:55,510
The next morning.

1299
00:55:56,070 --> 00:55:57,770
Smelled of coffee and warm bread.

1300
00:55:58,290 --> 00:56:00,950
The Savannah light came in from the side through the high window,

1301
00:56:01,450 --> 00:56:02,910
cut into bands by the frames,

1302
00:56:03,470 --> 00:56:05,570
and fell gold and over the white tablecloth,

1303
00:56:05,950 --> 00:56:08,630
over the cups, over the still warm loaves that

1304
00:56:08,630 --> 00:56:09,770
neither had left in a basket,

1305
00:56:10,270 --> 00:56:12,390
and disappeared before anyone could thank her.

1306
00:56:12,510 --> 00:56:14,090
That was how Nive did things,

1307
00:56:14,090 --> 00:56:16,410
beforehand and without making noise.

1308
00:56:16,950 --> 00:56:18,890
Roena sat with her legs crossed in the chair,

1309
00:56:19,290 --> 00:56:20,990
the cup warming both her hands.

1310
00:56:21,550 --> 00:56:25,690
Jego sat beside her, so close that his knee touched hers under the table.

1311
00:56:26,150 --> 00:56:26,890
He didn't speak.

1312
00:56:27,270 --> 00:56:30,310
He just extended his hand over the white tablecloth and waited.

1313
00:56:30,870 --> 00:56:32,410
Roena placed hers on top.

1314
00:56:32,750 --> 00:56:33,690
They stayed that way.

1315
00:56:34,110 --> 00:56:34,590
Unhurried.

1316
00:56:35,110 --> 00:56:38,430
While the heat of the coffee rose in a thread of steam between them.

1317
00:56:38,570 --> 00:56:39,490
She looked at the cup.

1318
00:56:39,810 --> 00:56:41,830
He had made the coffee the way she liked it.

1319
00:56:42,130 --> 00:56:43,250
Two dashes of sugar.

1320
00:56:43,250 --> 00:56:45,650
More milk than any barista would accept.

1321
00:56:46,070 --> 00:56:47,250
He'd made it without asking.

1322
00:56:47,730 --> 00:56:50,010
She smiled into the cup and said nothing,

1323
00:56:50,510 --> 00:56:51,770
because she didn't need to.

1324
00:56:52,050 --> 00:56:53,310
From the other side of the kitchen,

1325
00:56:53,690 --> 00:56:56,490
through the arch doorway you could see the corner of the main hall.

1326
00:56:56,930 --> 00:56:59,270
And from there you could see the empty chair near the window.

1327
00:56:59,750 --> 00:57:02,090
Its back was still turned slightly to the side,

1328
00:57:02,450 --> 00:57:04,190
as it had been the afternoon before,

1329
00:57:04,650 --> 00:57:07,310
as on every morning Roena had spent in that house.

1330
00:57:07,710 --> 00:57:09,790
No one had moved the chair during the night.

1331
00:57:10,210 --> 00:57:12,430
No one had occupied it as far as she knew.

1332
00:57:12,430 --> 00:57:14,770
On any of the times she'd been there.

1333
00:57:15,070 --> 00:57:15,470
Alaf.

1334
00:57:16,010 --> 00:57:17,390
Someone you'd orah had known.

1335
00:57:17,890 --> 00:57:19,270
Someone Jago had known.

1336
00:57:19,730 --> 00:57:22,090
A name the house had decided to stop saying,

1337
00:57:22,550 --> 00:57:25,750
guarded with such care that even the silence around it had shape.

1338
00:57:26,390 --> 00:57:27,490
Roena opened her mouth.

1339
00:57:28,010 --> 00:57:28,570
Jago.

1340
00:57:28,950 --> 00:57:30,410
He lifted his eyes from the coffee.

1341
00:57:30,890 --> 00:57:31,510
He didn't answer.

1342
00:57:32,110 --> 00:57:33,570
Yesterday she said,

1343
00:57:33,870 --> 00:57:36,230
and her voice came out soft, calibrated,

1344
00:57:36,770 --> 00:57:38,090
so as not to break that morning.

1345
00:57:38,550 --> 00:57:39,730
Your mother said something.

1346
00:57:40,210 --> 00:57:40,990
About a laugh.

1347
00:57:40,990 --> 00:57:43,910
Jago's hand overhears tightened a little.

1348
00:57:44,270 --> 00:57:44,890
That was all.

1349
00:57:45,350 --> 00:57:49,890
A small involuntary squeeze the kind that happens before a person decides to do it.

1350
00:57:50,110 --> 00:57:50,330
Boo!

1351
00:57:50,790 --> 00:57:51,570
She didn't finish.

1352
00:57:52,070 --> 00:57:54,050
Not because he interrupted her with any word.

1353
00:57:54,410 --> 00:57:56,070
It was the silence that did the work.

1354
00:57:56,450 --> 00:57:59,210
A whole round silence that filled the table and the coffee,

1355
00:57:59,690 --> 00:58:01,770
and the savanna light falling between them,

1356
00:58:01,970 --> 00:58:03,670
as if the sun too were waiting.

1357
00:58:04,270 --> 00:58:05,250
He looked at the cup,

1358
00:58:05,630 --> 00:58:07,110
then at her hand under his hand.

1359
00:58:07,490 --> 00:58:10,470
Then for a very brief instant at the empty chair far off

1360
00:58:10,470 --> 00:58:11,430
golden in the morning.

1361
00:58:11,850 --> 00:58:12,630
He didn't answer.

1362
00:58:13,170 --> 00:58:15,650
Roena felt then with a cold and new certainty

1363
00:58:15,650 --> 00:58:18,890
that there was an entire story living inside that house,

1364
00:58:19,350 --> 00:58:21,150
not in the walls or the old furniture,

1365
00:58:21,750 --> 00:58:24,830
but in the people who lived in it and carried it without saying the name.

1366
00:58:25,270 --> 00:58:26,870
She had just knocked on the right door.

1367
00:58:27,310 --> 00:58:29,370
The door was not going to open that morning.

1368
00:58:29,710 --> 00:58:31,450
She stored the question in her throat.

1369
00:58:31,830 --> 00:58:34,610
The way she had always stored what didn't yet have its time.

1370
00:58:34,990 --> 00:58:36,790
She closed her hand around his.

1371
00:58:37,130 --> 00:58:39,910
Outside a bird sang a high note and flew away.

1372
00:58:39,910 --> 00:58:41,810
The empty chair remained empty,

1373
00:58:42,350 --> 00:58:43,250
golden in the sun,

1374
00:58:43,610 --> 00:58:45,390
occupying the place it had always occupied,

1375
00:58:45,950 --> 00:58:48,550
and she understood without anyone needing to say it,

1376
00:58:48,810 --> 00:58:52,090
that that morning of peace was only the beginning of something else.

1377
00:58:54,420 --> 00:58:57,120
Hey Roen here, that's it for Book 1, but guess what?

1378
00:58:57,540 --> 00:58:58,480
Book 2 is already done.

1379
00:58:58,900 --> 00:59:01,280
You can grab access to it for just a small fee.

1380
00:59:06,670 --> 00:59:10,150
Six months later, she woke up every day in Jago's arms.

1381
00:59:10,610 --> 00:59:13,090
In the dream house he had built for the two of them.

1382
00:59:13,090 --> 00:59:15,650
Slow kisses, whispered promises,

1383
00:59:16,150 --> 00:59:20,150
his body fitted to hers as if the world outside didn't exist.

1384
00:59:20,790 --> 00:59:23,890
Until the bodyguard started following her into the more bathroom.

1385
00:59:24,790 --> 00:59:27,550
Until he deleted the job offer that had come for her,

1386
00:59:27,610 --> 00:59:28,630
without saying a word.

1387
00:59:29,090 --> 00:59:30,570
Until the phone rang and a name,

1388
00:59:31,110 --> 00:59:33,110
a name no one in that family dare to speak,

1389
00:59:33,650 --> 00:59:36,370
may Jago go pale, hang up mid-sentence,

1390
00:59:36,890 --> 00:59:39,410
and lie with his eyes still glazed with dread.

1391
00:59:40,390 --> 00:59:42,070
She saw the raw fear there.

1392
00:59:42,070 --> 00:59:46,450
The same fear he had been hiding since the night they kissed for the first time,

1393
00:59:46,790 --> 00:59:48,250
pretending it was only a game.

1394
00:59:48,910 --> 00:59:51,310
The old secret between them was no longer a shadow.

1395
00:59:51,830 --> 00:59:52,970
It was an open wound.

1396
00:59:53,550 --> 00:59:56,650
Capable of explaining the controlling man Jago had become,

1397
00:59:57,090 --> 00:59:59,570
and of destroying forever the man she had loved.

1398
00:59:59,870 --> 01:00:02,170
Now she trembled alone in the luxurious bedroom,

1399
01:00:02,690 --> 01:00:04,990
tasting the bitter flavor of betrayed trust.

1400
01:00:05,710 --> 01:00:07,890
And what if the past he had locked away with guilt

1401
01:00:07,890 --> 01:00:10,550
was greater than the love he swore he felt.

1402
01:00:10,550 --> 01:00:13,950
And what if opening that door made him hate her forever?

1403
01:00:14,390 --> 01:00:18,830
And what if the beautiful golden cage was the only thing still keeping the two of them together?

1404
